DeliveryChargeSpecification.name: DeliveryChargeSpecification
DeliveryChargeSpecification.help: The price for the delivery of an offer using a particular delivery method.

inputs.name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
inputs.label: Applies To Delivery Method
inputs.help: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.label: Area Served
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: eligibleRegion
inputs.label: Eligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.label: Ineligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

DeliveryMethod.name: DeliveryMethod
DeliveryMethod.help:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

WebPage.name: WebPage
WebPage.help: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

inputs.name: breadcrumb
inputs.label: Breadcrumb
inputs.help: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

inputs.name: lastReviewed
inputs.label: Last Reviewed
inputs.help: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

inputs.name: mainContentOfPage
inputs.label: Main Content Of Page
inputs.help: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

inputs.name: primaryImageOfPage
inputs.label: Primary Image Of Page
inputs.help: Indicates the main image on the page.

inputs.name: relatedLink
inputs.label: Related Link
inputs.help: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

inputs.name: reviewedBy
inputs.label: Reviewed By
inputs.help: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

inputs.name: significantLink
inputs.label: Significant Link
inputs.help: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

inputs.name: significantLinks
inputs.label: Significant Links
inputs.help: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

inputs.name: speakable
inputs.label: Speakable
inputs.help:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

inputs.name: specialty
inputs.label: Specialty
inputs.help: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

PodcastSeason.name: PodcastSeason
PodcastSeason.help: A single season of a podcast. Many podcasts do not break down into separate seasons. In that case, PodcastSeries should be used.

PublicationVolume.name: PublicationVolume
PublicationVolume.help: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/09/schemaorg-support-for-bibliographic_2.html).

inputs.name: pageEnd
inputs.label: Page End
inputs.help: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

inputs.name: pageStart
inputs.label: Page Start
inputs.help: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

inputs.name: pagination
inputs.label: Pagination
inputs.help: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

inputs.name: volumeNumber
inputs.label: Volume Number
inputs.help: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

Person.name: Person
Person.help: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

inputs.name: additionalName
inputs.label: Additional Name
inputs.help: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

inputs.name: address
inputs.label: Address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: affiliation
inputs.label: Affiliation
inputs.help: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

inputs.name: agentInteractionStatistic
inputs.label: Agent Interaction Statistic
inputs.help: The number of completed interactions for this entity, in a particular role (the 'agent'), in a particular action (indicated in the statistic), and in a particular context (i.e. interactionService).

inputs.name: alumniOf
inputs.label: Alumni Of
inputs.help: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

inputs.name: award
inputs.label: Award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: awards
inputs.label: Awards
inputs.help: Awards won by or for this item.

inputs.name: birthDate
inputs.label: Birth Date
inputs.help: Date of birth.

inputs.name: birthPlace
inputs.label: Birth Place
inputs.help: The place where the person was born.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.label: Brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: callSign
inputs.label: Call Sign
inputs.help: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

inputs.name: children
inputs.label: Children
inputs.help: A child of the person.

inputs.name: colleague
inputs.label: Colleague
inputs.help: A colleague of the person.

inputs.name: colleagues
inputs.label: Colleagues
inputs.help: A colleague of the person.

inputs.name: contactPoint
inputs.label: Contact Point
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: contactPoints
inputs.label: Contact Points
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: deathDate
inputs.label: Death Date
inputs.help: Date of death.

inputs.name: deathPlace
inputs.label: Death Place
inputs.help: The place where the person died.

inputs.name: duns
inputs.label: Duns
inputs.help: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

inputs.name: email
inputs.label: Email
inputs.help: Email address.

inputs.name: familyName
inputs.label: Family Name
inputs.help: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

inputs.name: faxNumber
inputs.label: Fax Number
inputs.help: The fax number.

inputs.name: follows
inputs.label: Follows
inputs.help: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

inputs.name: funder
inputs.label: Funder
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

inputs.name: funding
inputs.label: Funding
inputs.help: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

inputs.name: gender
inputs.label: Gender
inputs.help: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

inputs.name: givenName
inputs.label: Given Name
inputs.help: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

inputs.name: globalLocationNumber
inputs.label: Global Location Number
inputs.help: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

inputs.name: hasCertification
inputs.label: Has Certification
inputs.help: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

inputs.name: hasCredential
inputs.label: Has Credential
inputs.help: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

inputs.name: hasOccupation
inputs.label: Has Occupation
inputs.help: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

inputs.name: hasOfferCatalog
inputs.label: Has Offer Catalog
inputs.help: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

inputs.name: hasPOS
inputs.label: Has POS
inputs.help: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

inputs.name: height
inputs.label: Height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: homeLocation
inputs.label: Home Location
inputs.help: A contact location for a person's residence.

inputs.name: honorificPrefix
inputs.label: Honorific Prefix
inputs.help: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

inputs.name: honorificSuffix
inputs.label: Honorific Suffix
inputs.help: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D./PhD/MSCSW.

inputs.name: interactionStatistic
inputs.label: Interaction Statistic
inputs.help: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

inputs.name: isicV4
inputs.label: Isic V 4
inputs.help: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

inputs.name: jobTitle
inputs.label: Job Title
inputs.help: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

inputs.name: knows
inputs.label: Knows
inputs.help: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

inputs.name: knowsAbout
inputs.label: Knows About
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

inputs.name: knowsLanguage
inputs.label: Knows Language
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

inputs.name: makesOffer
inputs.label: Makes Offer
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

inputs.name: memberOf
inputs.label: Member Of
inputs.help: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

inputs.name: naics
inputs.label: Naics
inputs.help: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

inputs.name: nationality
inputs.label: Nationality
inputs.help: Nationality of the person.

inputs.name: netWorth
inputs.label: Net Worth
inputs.help: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

inputs.name: owns
inputs.label: Owns
inputs.help: Products owned by the organization or person.

inputs.name: parent
inputs.label: Parent
inputs.help: A parent of this person.

inputs.name: parents
inputs.label: Parents
inputs.help: A parents of the person.

inputs.name: performerIn
inputs.label: Performer In
inputs.help: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

inputs.name: publishingPrinciples
inputs.label: Publishing Principles
inputs.help:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

inputs.name: relatedTo
inputs.label: Related To
inputs.help: The most generic familial relation.

inputs.name: seeks
inputs.label: Seeks
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

inputs.name: sibling
inputs.label: Sibling
inputs.help: A sibling of the person.

inputs.name: siblings
inputs.label: Siblings
inputs.help: A sibling of the person.

inputs.name: sponsor
inputs.label: Sponsor
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

inputs.name: spouse
inputs.label: Spouse
inputs.help: The person's spouse.

inputs.name: taxID
inputs.label: Tax ID
inputs.help: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

inputs.name: telephone
inputs.label: Telephone
inputs.help: The telephone number.

inputs.name: vatID
inputs.label: Vat ID
inputs.help: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

inputs.name: weight
inputs.label: Weight
inputs.help: The weight of the product or person.

inputs.name: workLocation
inputs.label: Work Location
inputs.help: A contact location for a person's place of work.

inputs.name: worksFor
inputs.label: Works For
inputs.help: Organizations that the person works for.

Intangible.name: Intangible
Intangible.help: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

MediaGallery.name: MediaGallery
MediaGallery.help: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contain media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

MedicalEnumeration.name: MedicalEnumeration
MedicalEnumeration.help: Enumerations related to health and the practice of medicine: A concept that is used to attribute a quality to another concept, as a qualifier, a collection of items or a listing of all of the elements of a set in medicine practice.

DataType.name: DataType
DataType.help: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

UserPageVisits.name: UserPageVisits
UserPageVisits.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

ConfirmAction.name: ConfirmAction
ConfirmAction.help:
The act of notifying someone that a future event/action is going to happen as expected.

Related actions:

* [[CancelAction]]: The antonym of ConfirmAction.

CheckInAction.name: CheckInAction
CheckInAction.help:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check-in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).

Related actions:

* [[CheckOutAction]]: The antonym of CheckInAction.
* [[ArriveAction]]: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
* [[ConfirmAction]]: Unlike ConfirmAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the *start* of a previously reserved service rather than its validity/existence.

DefenceEstablishment.name: DefenceEstablishment
DefenceEstablishment.help: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

MedicalWebPage.name: MedicalWebPage
MedicalWebPage.help: A web page that provides medical information.

inputs.name: aspect
inputs.label: Aspect
inputs.help: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

inputs.name: medicalAudience
inputs.label: Medical Audience
inputs.help: Medical audience for page.

AccountingService.name: AccountingService
AccountingService.help: Accountancy business.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

MobileApplication.name: MobileApplication
MobileApplication.help: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

inputs.name: carrierRequirements
inputs.label: Carrier Requirements
inputs.help: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

Role.name: Role
Role.help: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/06/introducing-role.html).

inputs.name: endDate
inputs.label: End Date
inputs.help: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: namedPosition
inputs.label: Named Position
inputs.help: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

inputs.name: roleName
inputs.label: Role Name
inputs.help: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

inputs.name: startDate
inputs.label: Start Date
inputs.help: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

MedicalRiskScore.name: MedicalRiskScore
MedicalRiskScore.help: A simple system that adds up the number of risk factors to yield a score that is associated with prognosis, e.g. CHAD score, TIMI risk score.

inputs.name: algorithm
inputs.label: Algorithm
inputs.help: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

AdministrativeArea.name: AdministrativeArea
AdministrativeArea.help: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

WarrantyPromise.name: WarrantyPromise
WarrantyPromise.help: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

inputs.name: durationOfWarranty
inputs.label: Duration Of Warranty
inputs.help: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

inputs.name: warrantyScope
inputs.label: Warranty Scope
inputs.help: The scope of the warranty promise.

HealthPlanFormulary.name: HealthPlanFormulary
HealthPlanFormulary.help: For a given health insurance plan, the specification for costs and coverage of prescription drugs.

inputs.name: healthPlanCostSharing
inputs.label: Health Plan Cost Sharing
inputs.help: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

inputs.name: healthPlanDrugTier
inputs.label: Health Plan Drug Tier
inputs.help: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

inputs.name: offersPrescriptionByMail
inputs.label: Offers Prescription By Mail
inputs.help: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

MedicalProcedureType.name: MedicalProcedureType
MedicalProcedureType.help: An enumeration that describes different types of medical procedures.

TypeAndQuantityNode.name: TypeAndQuantityNode
TypeAndQuantityNode.help: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

inputs.name: amountOfThisGood
inputs.label: Amount Of This Good
inputs.help: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

inputs.name: businessFunction
inputs.label: Business Function
inputs.help: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

inputs.name: typeOfGood
inputs.label: Type Of Good
inputs.help: The product that this structured value is referring to.

inputs.name: unitCode
inputs.label: Unit Code
inputs.help: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

inputs.name: unitText
inputs.label: Unit Text
inputs.help: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

OwnershipInfo.name: OwnershipInfo
OwnershipInfo.help: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

inputs.name: acquiredFrom
inputs.label: Acquired From
inputs.help: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

inputs.name: ownedFrom
inputs.label: Owned From
inputs.help: The date and time of obtaining the product.

inputs.name: ownedThrough
inputs.label: Owned Through
inputs.help: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

inputs.name: typeOfGood
inputs.label: Type Of Good
inputs.help: The product that this structured value is referring to.

Game.name: Game
Game.help: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting.

inputs.name: characterAttribute
inputs.label: Character Attribute
inputs.help: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

inputs.name: gameItem
inputs.label: Game Item
inputs.help: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

inputs.name: gameLocation
inputs.label: Game Location
inputs.help: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

inputs.name: numberOfPlayers
inputs.label: Number Of Players
inputs.help: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

inputs.name: quest
inputs.label: Quest
inputs.help: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

DeactivateAction.name: DeactivateAction
DeactivateAction.help: The act of stopping or deactivating a device or application (e.g. stopping a timer or turning off a flashlight).

RsvpResponseType.name: RsvpResponseType
RsvpResponseType.help: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

CategoryCodeSet.name: CategoryCodeSet
CategoryCodeSet.help: A set of Category Code values.

inputs.name: hasCategoryCode
inputs.label: Has Category Code
inputs.help: A Category code contained in this code set.

ListenAction.name: ListenAction
ListenAction.help: The act of consuming audio content.

inputs.name: inLanguage
inputs.label: In Language
inputs.help: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

inputs.name: phoneticText
inputs.label: Phonetic Text
inputs.help: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

inputs.name: speechToTextMarkup
inputs.label: Speech To Text Markup
inputs.help: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

inputs.name: textValue
inputs.label: Text Value
inputs.help: Text value being annotated.

GovernmentBenefitsType.name: GovernmentBenefitsType
GovernmentBenefitsType.help: GovernmentBenefitsType enumerates several kinds of government benefits to support the COVID-19 situation. Note that this structure may not capture all benefits offered.

ComputerLanguage.name: ComputerLanguage
ComputerLanguage.help: This type covers computer programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, as well as other language-like computer representations. Natural languages are best represented with the [[Language]] type.

BodyOfWater.name: BodyOfWater
BodyOfWater.help: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

Place.name: Place
Place.help: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

inputs.name: additionalProperty
inputs.label: Additional Property
inputs.help: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

inputs.name: address
inputs.label: Address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: amenityFeature
inputs.label: Amenity Feature
inputs.help: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

inputs.name: branchCode
inputs.label: Branch Code
inputs.help: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

inputs.name: containedIn
inputs.label: Contained In
inputs.help: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

inputs.name: containedInPlace
inputs.label: Contained In Place
inputs.help: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

inputs.name: containsPlace
inputs.label: Contains Place
inputs.help: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

inputs.name: event
inputs.label: Event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

inputs.name: events
inputs.label: Events
inputs.help: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

inputs.name: faxNumber
inputs.label: Fax Number
inputs.help: The fax number.

inputs.name: geo
inputs.label: Geo
inputs.help: The geo coordinates of the place.

inputs.name: geoContains
inputs.label: Geo Contains
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoCoveredBy
inputs.label: Geo Covered By
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoCovers
inputs.label: Geo Covers
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoCrosses
inputs.label: Geo Crosses
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoDisjoint
inputs.label: Geo Disjoint
inputs.help: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

inputs.name: geoEquals
inputs.label: Geo Equals
inputs.help: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

inputs.name: geoIntersects
inputs.label: Geo Intersects
inputs.help: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoOverlaps
inputs.label: Geo Overlaps
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: geoTouches
inputs.label: Geo Touches
inputs.help: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

inputs.name: geoWithin
inputs.label: Geo Within
inputs.help: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inputs.name: globalLocationNumber
inputs.label: Global Location Number
inputs.help: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

inputs.name: hasCertification
inputs.label: Has Certification
inputs.help: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

inputs.name: hasDriveThroughService
inputs.label: Has Drive Through Service
inputs.help: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

inputs.name: hasGS1DigitalLink
inputs.label: Has GS 1 Digital Link
inputs.help:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

inputs.name: hasMap
inputs.label: Has Map
inputs.help: A URL to a map of the place.

inputs.name: isAccessibleForFree
inputs.label: Is Accessible For Free
inputs.help: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

inputs.name: isicV4
inputs.label: Isic V 4
inputs.help: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

inputs.name: keywords
inputs.label: Keywords
inputs.help: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

inputs.name: latitude
inputs.label: Latitude
inputs.help: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: longitude
inputs.label: Longitude
inputs.help: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

inputs.name: map
inputs.label: Map
inputs.help: A URL to a map of the place.

inputs.name: maps
inputs.label: Maps
inputs.help: A URL to a map of the place.

inputs.name: maximumAttendeeCapacity
inputs.label: Maximum Attendee Capacity
inputs.help: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

inputs.name: openingHoursSpecification
inputs.label: Opening Hours Specification
inputs.help: The opening hours of a certain place.

inputs.name: photo
inputs.label: Photo
inputs.help: A photograph of this place.

inputs.name: photos
inputs.label: Photos
inputs.help: Photographs of this place.

inputs.name: publicAccess
inputs.label: Public Access
inputs.help: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value.

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.label: Reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.label: Slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: smokingAllowed
inputs.label: Smoking Allowed
inputs.help: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

inputs.name: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
inputs.label: Special Opening Hours Specification
inputs.help: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

inputs.name: telephone
inputs.label: Telephone
inputs.help: The telephone number.

inputs.name: tourBookingPage
inputs.label: Tour Booking Page
inputs.help: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

ResearchOrganization.name: ResearchOrganization
ResearchOrganization.help: A Research Organization (e.g. scientific institute, research company).

UserPlusOnes.name: UserPlusOnes
UserPlusOnes.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

SchoolDistrict.name: SchoolDistrict
SchoolDistrict.help: A School District is an administrative area for the administration of schools.

CDCPMDRecord.name: CDCPMDRecord
CDCPMDRecord.help:
A CDCPMDRecord is a data structure representing a record in a CDC tabular data format
      used for hospital data reporting. See [documentation](/docs/cdc-covid.html) for details, and the linked CDC materials for authoritative
      definitions used as the source here.

inputs.name: cvdCollectionDate
inputs.label: Cvd Collection Date
inputs.help: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

inputs.name: cvdFacilityCounty
inputs.label: Cvd Facility County
inputs.help: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

inputs.name: cvdFacilityId
inputs.label: Cvd Facility Id
inputs.help: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

inputs.name: cvdNumBeds
inputs.label: Cvd Num Beds
inputs.help: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

inputs.name: cvdNumBedsOcc
inputs.label: Cvd Num Beds Occ
inputs.help: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19Died
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 Died
inputs.help: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19HOPats
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 HO Pats
inputs.help: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19HospPats
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 Hosp Pats
inputs.help: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 Mech Vent Pats
inputs.help: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 OF Mech Vent Pats
inputs.help: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
inputs.label: Cvd Num C 19 Overflow Pats
inputs.help: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

inputs.name: cvdNumICUBeds
inputs.label: Cvd Num ICU Beds
inputs.help: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

inputs.name: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
inputs.label: Cvd Num ICU Beds Occ
inputs.help: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

inputs.name: cvdNumTotBeds
inputs.label: Cvd Num Tot Beds
inputs.help: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

inputs.name: cvdNumVent
inputs.label: Cvd Num Vent
inputs.help: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

inputs.name: cvdNumVentUse
inputs.label: Cvd Num Vent Use
inputs.help: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

inputs.name: datePosted
inputs.label: Date Posted
inputs.help: Publication date of an online listing.

LegislativeBuilding.name: LegislativeBuilding
LegislativeBuilding.help: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

CoverArt.name: CoverArt
CoverArt.help: The artwork on the outer surface of a CreativeWork.

Consortium.name: Consortium
Consortium.help: A Consortium is a membership [[Organization]] whose members are typically Organizations.

VacationRental.name: VacationRental
VacationRental.help: A kind of lodging business that focuses on renting single properties for limited time.

ShippingRateSettings.name: ShippingRateSettings
ShippingRateSettings.help: A ShippingRateSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of an [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished and matched (i.e. identified/referenced) by their different values for [[shippingLabel]].

inputs.name: doesNotShip
inputs.label: Does Not Ship
inputs.help: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

inputs.name: freeShippingThreshold
inputs.label: Free Shipping Threshold
inputs.help: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

inputs.name: isUnlabelledFallback
inputs.label: Is Unlabelled Fallback
inputs.help: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

inputs.name: shippingDestination
inputs.label: Shipping Destination
inputs.help: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

inputs.name: shippingLabel
inputs.label: Shipping Label
inputs.help: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[ShippingRateSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

inputs.name: shippingRate
inputs.label: Shipping Rate
inputs.help: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

inputs.name: alumni
inputs.label: Alumni
inputs.help: Alumni of an organization.

OrderAction.name: OrderAction
OrderAction.help: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

inputs.name: deliveryMethod
inputs.label: Delivery Method
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

Permit.name: Permit
Permit.help: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

inputs.name: issuedBy
inputs.label: Issued By
inputs.help: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

inputs.name: issuedThrough
inputs.label: Issued Through
inputs.help: The service through which the permit was granted.

inputs.name: permitAudience
inputs.label: Permit Audience
inputs.help: The target audience for this permit.

inputs.name: validFor
inputs.label: Valid For
inputs.help: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.label: Valid From
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validIn
inputs.label: Valid In
inputs.help: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

inputs.name: validUntil
inputs.label: Valid Until
inputs.help: The date when the item is no longer valid.

MediaReview.name: MediaReview
MediaReview.help:
A [[MediaReview]] is a more specialized form of Review dedicated to the evaluation of media content online, typically in the context of fact-checking and misinformation.
    For more general reviews of media in the broader sense, use [[UserReview]], [[CriticReview]] or other [[Review]] types. This definition is
    a work in progress. While the [[MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration]] list reflects significant community review amongst fact-checkers and others working
    to combat misinformation, the specific structures for representing media objects, their versions and publication context, are still evolving. Similarly, best practices for the relationship between [[MediaReview]] and [[ClaimReview]] markup have not yet been finalized.

inputs.name: mediaAuthenticityCategory
inputs.label: Media Authenticity Category
inputs.help: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

inputs.name: originalMediaContextDescription
inputs.label: Original Media Context Description
inputs.help: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

inputs.name: originalMediaLink
inputs.label: Original Media Link
inputs.help: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

RejectAction.name: RejectAction
RejectAction.help:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[AcceptAction]]: The antonym of RejectAction.

MusicRelease.name: MusicRelease
MusicRelease.help: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

inputs.name: catalogNumber
inputs.label: Catalog Number
inputs.help: The catalog number for the release.

inputs.name: creditedTo
inputs.label: Credited To
inputs.help: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: musicReleaseFormat
inputs.label: Music Release Format
inputs.help: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

inputs.name: recordLabel
inputs.label: Record Label
inputs.help: The label that issued the release.

inputs.name: releaseOf
inputs.label: Release Of
inputs.help: The album this is a release of.

MedicalCode.name: MedicalCode
MedicalCode.help: A code for a medical entity.

inputs.name: codeValue
inputs.label: Code Value
inputs.help: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

inputs.name: codingSystem
inputs.label: Coding System
inputs.help: The coding system, e.g. 'ICD-10'.

RealEstateListing.name: RealEstateListing
RealEstateListing.help:
A [[RealEstateListing]] is a listing that describes one or more real-estate [[Offer]]s (whose [[businessFunction]] is typically to lease out, or to sell).
  The [[RealEstateListing]] type itself represents the overall listing, as manifested in some [[WebPage]].

inputs.name: datePosted
inputs.label: Date Posted
inputs.help: Publication date of an online listing.

inputs.name: leaseLength
inputs.label: Lease Length
inputs.help: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

Property.name: Property
Property.help: A property, used to indicate attributes and relationships of some Thing; equivalent to rdf:Property.

inputs.name: domainIncludes
inputs.label: Domain Includes
inputs.help: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

inputs.name: inverseOf
inputs.label: Inverse Of
inputs.help: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

inputs.name: rangeIncludes
inputs.label: Range Includes
inputs.help: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

inputs.name: supersededBy
inputs.label: Superseded By
inputs.help: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

ItemAvailability.name: ItemAvailability
ItemAvailability.help: A list of possible product availability options.

TravelAction.name: TravelAction
TravelAction.help: The act of traveling from a fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

inputs.name: distance
inputs.label: Distance
inputs.help: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

BuyAction.name: BuyAction
BuyAction.help: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.label: Seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

inputs.name: vendor
inputs.label: Vendor
inputs.help: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

inputs.name: warrantyPromise
inputs.label: Warranty Promise
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

FundingAgency.name: FundingAgency
FundingAgency.help:
A FundingAgency is an organization that implements one or more [[FundingScheme]]s and manages
    the granting process (via [[Grant]]s, typically [[MonetaryGrant]]s).
    A funding agency is not always required for grant funding, e.g. philanthropic giving, corporate sponsorship etc.
    
Examples of funding agencies include ERC, REA, NIH, Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, ...

HowToDirection.name: HowToDirection
HowToDirection.help: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.

inputs.name: afterMedia
inputs.label: After Media
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

inputs.name: beforeMedia
inputs.label: Before Media
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

inputs.name: duringMedia
inputs.label: During Media
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

inputs.name: performTime
inputs.label: Perform Time
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: prepTime
inputs.label: Prep Time
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: supply
inputs.label: Supply
inputs.help: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: tool
inputs.label: Tool
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: totalTime
inputs.label: Total Time
inputs.help: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

QAPage.name: QAPage
QAPage.help: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

LegalForceStatus.name: LegalForceStatus
LegalForceStatus.help: A list of possible statuses for the legal force of a legislation.

ReturnMethodEnumeration.name: ReturnMethodEnumeration
ReturnMethodEnumeration.help: Enumerates several types of product return methods.

AppendAction.name: AppendAction
AppendAction.help: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

inputs.name: monthsOfExperience
inputs.label: Months Of Experience
inputs.help: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

Distance.name: Distance
Distance.help: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

GameAvailabilityEnumeration.name: GameAvailabilityEnumeration
GameAvailabilityEnumeration.help: For a [[VideoGame]], such as used with a [[PlayGameAction]], an enumeration of the kind of game availability offered.

MedicalBusiness.name: MedicalBusiness
MedicalBusiness.help: A particular physical or virtual business of an organization for medical purposes. Examples of MedicalBusiness include different businesses run by health professionals.

PaymentCard.name: PaymentCard
PaymentCard.help: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.

inputs.name: cashBack
inputs.label: Cash Back
inputs.help: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

inputs.name: contactlessPayment
inputs.label: Contactless Payment
inputs.help: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

inputs.name: floorLimit
inputs.label: Floor Limit
inputs.help: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

inputs.name: monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
inputs.label: Monthly Minimum Repayment Amount
inputs.help: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

RadioSeason.name: RadioSeason
RadioSeason.help: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

UserCheckins.name: UserCheckins
UserCheckins.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

inputs.name: abridged
inputs.label: Abridged
inputs.help: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

inputs.name: bookEdition
inputs.label: Book Edition
inputs.help: The edition of the book.

inputs.name: bookFormat
inputs.label: Book Format
inputs.help: The format of the book.

inputs.name: illustrator
inputs.label: Illustrator
inputs.help: The illustrator of the book.

inputs.name: isbn
inputs.label: Isbn
inputs.help: The ISBN of the book.

inputs.name: numberOfPages
inputs.label: Number Of Pages
inputs.help: The number of pages in the book.

BedAndBreakfast.name: BedAndBreakfast
BedAndBreakfast.help:
Bed and breakfast.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

ReturnFeesEnumeration.name: ReturnFeesEnumeration
ReturnFeesEnumeration.help: Enumerates several kinds of policies for product return fees.

MedicalOrganization.name: MedicalOrganization
MedicalOrganization.help: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

inputs.name: healthPlanNetworkId
inputs.label: Health Plan Network Id
inputs.help: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

inputs.name: isAcceptingNewPatients
inputs.label: Is Accepting New Patients
inputs.help: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.label: Medical Specialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

inputs.name: composer
inputs.label: Composer
inputs.help: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

inputs.name: firstPerformance
inputs.label: First Performance
inputs.help: The date and place the work was first performed.

inputs.name: includedComposition
inputs.label: Included Composition
inputs.help: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

inputs.name: iswcCode
inputs.label: Iswc Code
inputs.help: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

inputs.name: lyricist
inputs.label: Lyricist
inputs.help: The person who wrote the words.

inputs.name: lyrics
inputs.label: Lyrics
inputs.help: The words in the song.

inputs.name: musicArrangement
inputs.label: Music Arrangement
inputs.help: An arrangement derived from the composition.

inputs.name: musicCompositionForm
inputs.label: Music Composition Form
inputs.help: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

inputs.name: musicalKey
inputs.label: Musical Key
inputs.help: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

inputs.name: recordedAs
inputs.label: Recorded As
inputs.help: An audio recording of the work.

ConstraintNode.name: ConstraintNode
ConstraintNode.help:
The ConstraintNode type is provided to support usecases in which a node in a structured data graph is described with properties which appear to describe a single entity, but are being used in a situation where they serve a more abstract purpose. A [[ConstraintNode]] can be described using [[constraintProperty]] and [[numConstraints]]. These constraint properties can serve a 
    variety of purposes, and their values may sometimes be understood to indicate sets of possible values rather than single, exact and specific values.

inputs.name: constraintProperty
inputs.label: Constraint Property
inputs.help: Indicates a property used as a constraint. For example, in the definition of a [[StatisticalVariable]]. The value is a property, either from within Schema.org or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

inputs.name: numConstraints
inputs.label: Num Constraints
inputs.help: Indicates the number of constraints property values defined for a particular [[ConstraintNode]] such as [[StatisticalVariable]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalVariable]] or other construct that is defined using properties on template-style nodes.

Order.name: Order
Order.help: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

inputs.name: acceptedOffer
inputs.label: Accepted Offer
inputs.help: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

inputs.name: billingAddress
inputs.label: Billing Address
inputs.help: The billing address for the order.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.label: Broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: confirmationNumber
inputs.label: Confirmation Number
inputs.help: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

inputs.name: customer
inputs.label: Customer
inputs.help: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

inputs.name: discount
inputs.label: Discount
inputs.help: Any discount applied (to an Order).

inputs.name: discountCode
inputs.label: Discount Code
inputs.help: Code used to redeem a discount.

inputs.name: discountCurrency
inputs.label: Discount Currency
inputs.help: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: isGift
inputs.label: Is Gift
inputs.help: Indicates whether the offer was accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

inputs.name: merchant
inputs.label: Merchant
inputs.help: 'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

inputs.name: orderDate
inputs.label: Order Date
inputs.help: Date order was placed.

inputs.name: orderDelivery
inputs.label: Order Delivery
inputs.help: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

inputs.name: orderNumber
inputs.label: Order Number
inputs.help: The identifier of the transaction.

inputs.name: orderStatus
inputs.label: Order Status
inputs.help: The current status of the order.

inputs.name: orderedItem
inputs.label: Ordered Item
inputs.help: The item ordered.

inputs.name: partOfInvoice
inputs.label: Part Of Invoice
inputs.help: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

inputs.name: paymentDue
inputs.label: Payment Due
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentDueDate
inputs.label: Payment Due Date
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentMethod
inputs.label: Payment Method
inputs.help: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

inputs.name: paymentMethodId
inputs.label: Payment Method Id
inputs.help: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

inputs.name: paymentUrl
inputs.label: Payment Url
inputs.help: The URL for sending a payment.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.label: Seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

PerformingGroup.name: PerformingGroup
PerformingGroup.help: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

inputs.name: awayTeam
inputs.label: Away Team
inputs.help: The away team in a sports event.

inputs.name: competitor
inputs.label: Competitor
inputs.help: A competitor in a sports event.

inputs.name: homeTeam
inputs.label: Home Team
inputs.help: The home team in a sports event.

inputs.name: sport
inputs.label: Sport
inputs.help: A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

Trip.name: Trip
Trip.help: A trip or journey. An itinerary of visits to one or more places.

inputs.name: arrivalTime
inputs.label: Arrival Time
inputs.help: The expected arrival time.

inputs.name: departureTime
inputs.label: Departure Time
inputs.help: The expected departure time.

inputs.name: itinerary
inputs.label: Itinerary
inputs.help: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

inputs.name: offers
inputs.label: Offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: partOfTrip
inputs.label: Part Of Trip
inputs.help: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.label: Provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: subTrip
inputs.label: Sub Trip
inputs.help: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

inputs.name: tripOrigin
inputs.label: Trip Origin
inputs.help: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

FoodEstablishmentReservation.name: FoodEstablishmentReservation
FoodEstablishmentReservation.help: A reservation to dine at a food-related business.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

inputs.name: endTime
inputs.label: End Time
inputs.help: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

inputs.name: partySize
inputs.label: Party Size
inputs.help: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

inputs.name: startTime
inputs.label: Start Time
inputs.help: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

Rating.name: Rating
Rating.help: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

inputs.name: author
inputs.label: Author
inputs.help: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

inputs.name: bestRating
inputs.label: Best Rating
inputs.help: The highest value allowed in this rating system.

inputs.name: ratingExplanation
inputs.label: Rating Explanation
inputs.help: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

inputs.name: ratingValue
inputs.label: Rating Value
inputs.help:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.label: Review Aspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

inputs.name: worstRating
inputs.label: Worst Rating
inputs.help: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

LibrarySystem.name: LibrarySystem
LibrarySystem.help: A [[LibrarySystem]] is a collaborative system amongst several libraries.

DataDownload.name: DataDownload
DataDownload.help: All or part of a [[Dataset]] in downloadable form.

inputs.name: measurementMethod
inputs.label: Measurement Method
inputs.help: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.label: Measurement Technique
inputs.help:
A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable.
    
The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. 

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". 

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

WearableMeasurementTypeEnumeration.name: WearableMeasurementTypeEnumeration
WearableMeasurementTypeEnumeration.help: Enumerates common types of measurement for wearables products.

MedicalContraindication.name: MedicalContraindication
MedicalContraindication.help: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

Course.name: Course
Course.help: A description of an educational course which may be offered as distinct instances which take place at different times or take place at different locations, or be offered through different media or modes of study. An educational course is a sequence of one or more educational events and/or creative works which aims to build knowledge, competence or ability of learners.

inputs.name: availableLanguage
inputs.label: Available Language
inputs.help: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

inputs.name: courseCode
inputs.label: Course Code
inputs.help: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

inputs.name: coursePrerequisites
inputs.label: Course Prerequisites
inputs.help: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

inputs.name: educationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.label: Educational Credential Awarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

inputs.name: financialAidEligible
inputs.label: Financial Aid Eligible
inputs.help: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

inputs.name: hasCourseInstance
inputs.label: Has Course Instance
inputs.help: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

inputs.name: numberOfCredits
inputs.label: Number Of Credits
inputs.help: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

inputs.name: occupationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.label: Occupational Credential Awarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

inputs.name: syllabusSections
inputs.label: Syllabus Sections
inputs.help: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

inputs.name: totalHistoricalEnrollment
inputs.label: Total Historical Enrollment
inputs.help: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

ChooseAction.name: ChooseAction
ChooseAction.help: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

inputs.name: actionOption
inputs.label: Action Option
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

inputs.name: option
inputs.label: Option
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

DiscussionForumPosting.name: DiscussionForumPosting
DiscussionForumPosting.help: A posting to a discussion forum.

LegalValueLevel.name: LegalValueLevel
LegalValueLevel.help: A list of possible levels for the legal validity of a legislation.

NLNonprofitType.name: NLNonprofitType
NLNonprofitType.help: NLNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the Netherlands.

WearAction.name: WearAction
WearAction.help: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

ReplyAction.name: ReplyAction
ReplyAction.help:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to [[AskAction]].

Related actions:

* [[AskAction]]: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

inputs.name: resultComment
inputs.label: Result Comment
inputs.help: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

SoftwareSourceCode.name: SoftwareSourceCode
SoftwareSourceCode.help: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

inputs.name: codeRepository
inputs.label: Code Repository
inputs.help: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

inputs.name: codeSampleType
inputs.label: Code Sample Type
inputs.help: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

inputs.name: programmingLanguage
inputs.label: Programming Language
inputs.help: The computer programming language.

inputs.name: runtime
inputs.label: Runtime
inputs.help: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

inputs.name: runtimePlatform
inputs.label: Runtime Platform
inputs.help: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

inputs.name: sampleType
inputs.label: Sample Type
inputs.help: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

inputs.name: targetProduct
inputs.label: Target Product
inputs.help: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

AssessAction.name: AssessAction
AssessAction.help: The act of forming one's opinion, reaction or sentiment.

Airline.name: Airline
Airline.help: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

inputs.name: boardingPolicy
inputs.label: Boarding Policy
inputs.help: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

inputs.name: iataCode
inputs.label: Iata Code
inputs.help: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

ProfessionalService.name: ProfessionalService
ProfessionalService.help:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."\n\nThe general [[ProfessionalService]] type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with [[Service]]. For reference, the types that it included were: [[Dentist]],
        [[AccountingService]], [[Attorney]], [[Notary]], as well as types for several kinds of [[HomeAndConstructionBusiness]]: [[Electrician]], [[GeneralContractor]],
        [[HousePainter]], [[Locksmith]], [[Plumber]], [[RoofingContractor]]. [[LegalService]] was introduced as a more inclusive supertype of [[Attorney]].

Reservoir.name: Reservoir
Reservoir.help: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

ImageGallery.name: ImageGallery
ImageGallery.help: Web page type: Image gallery page.

SheetMusic.name: SheetMusic
SheetMusic.help: Printed music, as opposed to performed or recorded music.

NonprofitType.name: NonprofitType
NonprofitType.help: NonprofitType enumerates several kinds of official non-profit types of which a non-profit organization can be.

ComicIssue.name: ComicIssue
ComicIssue.help:
Individual comic issues are serially published as
    	part of a larger series. For the sake of consistency, even one-shot issues
    	belong to a series comprised of a single issue. All comic issues can be
    	uniquely identified by: the combination of the name and volume number of the
    	series to which the issue belongs; the issue number; and the variant
    	description of the issue (if any).

inputs.name: artist
inputs.label: Artist
inputs.help:
The primary artist for a work
    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

inputs.name: colorist
inputs.label: Colorist
inputs.help: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

inputs.name: inker
inputs.label: Inker
inputs.help: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

inputs.name: letterer
inputs.label: Letterer
inputs.help: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

inputs.name: penciler
inputs.label: Penciler
inputs.help: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

inputs.name: variantCover
inputs.label: Variant Cover
inputs.help:
A description of the variant cover
    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch
    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

inputs.name: assesses
inputs.label: Assesses
