SearchRescueOrganization.help: A Search and Rescue organization of some kind.

OfferForPurchase.name: OfferForPurchase
OfferForPurchase.help:
An [[OfferForPurchase]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to sell something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [sell](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

inputs.name: endorsee
inputs.label: Endorsee
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

LegalService.name: LegalService
LegalService.help: A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

RadioSeries.name: RadioSeries
RadioSeries.help: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.label: Actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.label: Actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: containsSeason
inputs.label: Contains Season
inputs.help: A season that is part of the media series.

inputs.name: director
inputs.label: Director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.label: Directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: episode
inputs.label: Episode
inputs.help: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

inputs.name: episodes
inputs.label: Episodes
inputs.help: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.label: Music By
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: numberOfEpisodes
inputs.label: Number Of Episodes
inputs.help: The number of episodes in this season or series.

inputs.name: numberOfSeasons
inputs.label: Number Of Seasons
inputs.help: The number of seasons in this series.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.label: Production Company
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: season
inputs.label: Season
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: seasons
inputs.label: Seasons
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.label: Trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

ApplyAction.name: ApplyAction
ApplyAction.help:
The act of registering to an organization/service without the guarantee to receive it.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, ApplyAction has no guarantees that the application will be accepted.

OfferItemCondition.name: OfferItemCondition
OfferItemCondition.help: A list of possible conditions for the item.

Thing.name: Thing
Thing.help: The most generic type of item.

inputs.name: additionalType
inputs.label: Additional Type
inputs.help: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label should follow the schema.org style guide.

inputs.name: alternateName
inputs.label: Alternate Name
inputs.help: An alias for the item.

inputs.name: conformsTo
inputs.label: Conforms To
inputs.help: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

inputs.name: description
inputs.label: Description
inputs.help: A description of the item.

inputs.name: disambiguatingDescription
inputs.label: Disambiguating Description
inputs.help: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

inputs.name: hasCreationDate
inputs.label: Has Creation Date
inputs.help: Inverse of 'is creation date of' object property

inputs.name: hasModificationDate
inputs.label: Has Modification Date
inputs.help: Inverse of 'is modification date of' object property.

inputs.name: identifier
inputs.label: Identifier
inputs.help: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

inputs.name: image
inputs.label: Image
inputs.help: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

inputs.name: mainEntityOfPage
inputs.label: Main Entity Of Page
inputs.help: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

inputs.name: name
inputs.label: Name
inputs.help: The name of the item.

inputs.name: potentialAction
inputs.label: Potential Action
inputs.help: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

inputs.name: sameAs
inputs.label: Same As
inputs.help: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

inputs.name: subjectOf
inputs.label: Subject Of
inputs.help: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

inputs.name: thingIsConnectedToRelation
inputs.label: Is Connected To Relation
inputs.help: Connects a Thing to a n-ary Relation.

inputs.name: thingIsContextOfRelation
inputs.label: Is Context Of Relation
inputs.help: Connects a Thing (that is a secondary, contextual entity during the existence of the Relation) to a n-ary Relation.

inputs.name: thingIsSourceOfRelation
inputs.label: Is Source Of Relation
inputs.help: Connects a Thing (that is the source of a Relation) to a Relation.

inputs.name: thingIsTargetOfRelation
inputs.label: Is Target Of Relation
inputs.help: Connects a Thing (that is the target of a Relation) to a n-ary Relation.

inputs.name: url
inputs.label: Url
inputs.help: URL of the item.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: readBy
inputs.label: Read By
inputs.help: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

RegisterAction.name: RegisterAction
RegisterAction.help:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

ActionAccessSpecification.name: ActionAccessSpecification
ActionAccessSpecification.help: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action.

inputs.name: availabilityEnds
inputs.label: Availability Ends
inputs.help: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availabilityStarts
inputs.label: Availability Starts
inputs.help: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: eligibleRegion
inputs.label: Eligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: expectsAcceptanceOf
inputs.label: Expects Acceptance Of
inputs.help: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.label: Ineligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: requiresSubscription
inputs.label: Requires Subscription
inputs.help: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

Offer.name: Offer
Offer.help:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

Note: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.

For [GTIN](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin)-related fields, see [Check Digit calculator](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/support/check_digit_calculator) and [validation guide](http://www.gs1us.org/resources/standards/gtin-validation-guide) from [GS1](http://www.gs1.org/).

inputs.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
inputs.label: Accepted Payment Method
inputs.help: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

inputs.name: addOn
inputs.label: Add On
inputs.help: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

inputs.name: additionalProperty
inputs.label: Additional Property
inputs.help: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

inputs.name: advanceBookingRequirement
inputs.label: Advance Booking Requirement
inputs.help: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.label: Area Served
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: asin
inputs.label: Asin
inputs.help:
An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).

Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

inputs.name: availability
inputs.label: Availability
inputs.help: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

inputs.name: availabilityEnds
inputs.label: Availability Ends
inputs.help: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availabilityStarts
inputs.label: Availability Starts
inputs.help: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availableAtOrFrom
inputs.label: Available At Or From
inputs.help: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

inputs.name: availableDeliveryMethod
inputs.label: Available Delivery Method
inputs.help: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

inputs.name: businessFunction
inputs.label: Business Function
inputs.help: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: checkoutPageURLTemplate
inputs.label: Checkout Page URL Template
inputs.help: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

inputs.name: deliveryLeadTime
inputs.label: Delivery Lead Time
inputs.help: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

inputs.name: eligibleCustomerType
inputs.label: Eligible Customer Type
inputs.help: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleDuration
inputs.label: Eligible Duration
inputs.help: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleQuantity
inputs.label: Eligible Quantity
inputs.help: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

inputs.name: eligibleRegion
inputs.label: Eligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
inputs.label: Eligible Transaction Volume
inputs.help: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

inputs.name: gtin
inputs.label: Gtin
inputs.help:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties.

The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) expresses GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.).
Digital Links should be populated into the [[hasGS1DigitalLink]] attribute.

Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

inputs.name: gtin12
inputs.label: Gtin 12
inputs.help: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin13
inputs.label: Gtin 13
inputs.help: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin14
inputs.label: Gtin 14
inputs.help: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin8
inputs.label: Gtin 8
inputs.help: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: hasAdultConsideration
inputs.label: Has Adult Consideration
inputs.help: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

inputs.name: hasGS1DigitalLink
inputs.label: Has GS 1 Digital Link
inputs.help:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

inputs.name: hasMeasurement
inputs.label: Has Measurement
inputs.help: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

inputs.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
inputs.label: Has Merchant Return Policy
inputs.help: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

inputs.name: includesObject
inputs.label: Includes Object
inputs.help: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.label: Ineligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: inventoryLevel
inputs.label: Inventory Level
inputs.help: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

inputs.name: isFamilyFriendly
inputs.label: Is Family Friendly
inputs.help: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.label: Item Condition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: itemOffered
inputs.label: Item Offered
inputs.help: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: leaseLength
inputs.label: Lease Length
inputs.help: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

inputs.name: mobileUrl
inputs.label: Mobile Url
inputs.help:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

inputs.name: mpn
inputs.label: Mpn
inputs.help: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: offeredBy
inputs.label: Offered By
inputs.help: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

inputs.name: price
inputs.label: Price
inputs.help:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.label: Price Currency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: priceSpecification
inputs.label: Price Specification
inputs.help: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

inputs.name: priceValidUntil
inputs.label: Price Valid Until
inputs.help: The date after which the price is no longer available.

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.label: Reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.label: Seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

inputs.name: serialNumber
inputs.label: Serial Number
inputs.help: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

inputs.name: shippingDetails
inputs.label: Shipping Details
inputs.help: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

inputs.name: sku
inputs.label: Sku
inputs.help: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.label: Valid From
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.label: Valid Through
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: warranty
inputs.label: Warranty
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

MediaSubscription.name: MediaSubscription
MediaSubscription.help: A subscription which allows a user to access media including audio, video, books, etc.

inputs.name: authenticator
inputs.label: Authenticator
inputs.help: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

inputs.name: expectsAcceptanceOf
inputs.label: Expects Acceptance Of
inputs.help: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

BoatReservation.name: BoatReservation
BoatReservation.help:
A reservation for boat travel.

Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

CriticReview.name: CriticReview
CriticReview.help: A [[CriticReview]] is a more specialized form of Review written or published by a source that is recognized for its reviewing activities. These can include online columns, travel and food guides, TV and radio shows, blogs and other independent Web sites. [[CriticReview]]s are typically more in-depth and professionally written. For simpler, casually written user/visitor/viewer/customer reviews, it is more appropriate to use the [[UserReview]] type. Review aggregator sites such as Metacritic already separate out the site's user reviews from selected critic reviews that originate from third-party sources.

Certification.name: Certification
Certification.help: A Certification is an official and authoritative statement about a subject, for example a product, service, person, or organization. A certification is typically issued by an indendent certification body, for example a professional organization or government. It formally attests certain characteristics about the subject, for example Organizations can be ISO certified, Food products can be certified Organic or Vegan, a Person can be a certified professional, a Place can be certified for food processing. There are certifications for many domains: regulatory, organizational, recycling, food, efficiency, educational, ecological, etc. A certification is a form of credential, as are accreditations and licenses. Mapped from the [gs1:CertificationDetails](https://www.gs1.org/voc/CertificationDetails) class in the GS1 Web Vocabulary.

inputs.name: about
inputs.label: About
inputs.help: The subject matter of the content.

inputs.name: auditDate
inputs.label: Audit Date
inputs.help: Date when a certification was last audited. See also  [gs1:certificationAuditDate](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationAuditDate).

inputs.name: certificationIdentification
inputs.label: Certification Identification
inputs.help: Identifier of a certification instance (as registered with an independent certification body). Typically this identifier can be used to consult and verify the certification instance. See also [gs1:certificationIdentification](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationIdentification).

inputs.name: certificationRating
inputs.label: Certification Rating
inputs.help: Rating of a certification instance (as defined by an independent certification body). Typically this rating can be used to rate the level to which the requirements of the certification instance are fulfilled. See also [gs1:certificationValue](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationValue).

inputs.name: certificationStatus
inputs.label: Certification Status
inputs.help: Indicates the current status of a certification: active or inactive. See also  [gs1:certificationStatus](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationStatus).

inputs.name: datePublished
inputs.label: Date Published
inputs.help: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

inputs.name: expires
inputs.label: Expires
inputs.help: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

inputs.name: hasMeasurement
inputs.label: Has Measurement
inputs.help: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

inputs.name: issuedBy
inputs.label: Issued By
inputs.help: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.label: Valid From
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validIn
inputs.label: Valid In
inputs.help: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

CertificationStatusEnumeration.name: CertificationStatusEnumeration
CertificationStatusEnumeration.help: Enumerates the different statuses of a Certification (Active and Inactive).

Physician.name: Physician
Physician.help: An individual physician or a physician's office considered as a [[MedicalOrganization]].

inputs.name: availableService
inputs.label: Available Service
inputs.help: A medical service available from this provider.

inputs.name: hospitalAffiliation
inputs.label: Hospital Affiliation
inputs.help: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.label: Medical Specialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.label: Occupational Category
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: usNPI
inputs.label: Us NPI
inputs.help: A National Provider Identifier (NPI) is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.

BrainStructure.name: BrainStructure
BrainStructure.help: Any anatomical structure which pertains to the soft nervous tissue functioning as the coordinating center of sensation and intellectual and nervous activity.

Answer.name: Answer
Answer.help: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

inputs.name: answerExplanation
inputs.label: Answer Explanation
inputs.help: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

inputs.name: parentItem
inputs.label: Parent Item
inputs.help: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

FAQPage.name: FAQPage
FAQPage.help: A [[FAQPage]] is a [[WebPage]] presenting one or more "[Frequently asked questions](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)" (see also [[QAPage]]).

Joint.name: Joint
Joint.help: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

inputs.name: biomechnicalClass
inputs.label: Biomechnical Class
inputs.help: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

inputs.name: functionalClass
inputs.label: Functional Class
inputs.help: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

inputs.name: structuralClass
inputs.label: Structural Class
inputs.help: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

TradeAction.name: TradeAction
TradeAction.help: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

inputs.name: price
inputs.label: Price
inputs.help:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.label: Price Currency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: priceSpecification
inputs.label: Price Specification
inputs.help: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

MedicalSymptom.name: MedicalSymptom
MedicalSymptom.help: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective)  like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

WorkersUnion.name: WorkersUnion
WorkersUnion.help: A Workers Union (also known as a Labor Union, Labour Union, or Trade Union) is an organization that promotes the interests of its worker members by collectively bargaining with management, organizing, and political lobbying.

GamePlayMode.name: GamePlayMode
GamePlayMode.help: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

MusicAlbumProductionType.name: MusicAlbumProductionType
MusicAlbumProductionType.help: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

inputs.name: dataset
inputs.label: Dataset
inputs.help: A dataset contained in this catalog.

inputs.name: measurementMethod
inputs.label: Measurement Method
inputs.help: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.label: Measurement Technique
inputs.help:
A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable.
    
The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. 

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". 

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

PrependAction.name: PrependAction
PrependAction.help: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

BreadcrumbList.name: BreadcrumbList
BreadcrumbList.help: A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.\n\nThe [[position]] property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList. The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an [[itemListOrder]] of [[ItemListOrderAscending]] (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail, e.g. with a site or section homepage. The specific values of 'position' are not assigned meaning for a BreadcrumbList, but they should be integers, e.g. beginning with '1' for the first item in the list.

DataFeed.name: DataFeed
DataFeed.help: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.

inputs.name: dataFeedElement
inputs.label: Data Feed Element
inputs.help: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

PeopleAudience.name: PeopleAudience
PeopleAudience.help: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

inputs.name: healthCondition
inputs.label: Health Condition
inputs.help: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

inputs.name: requiredGender
inputs.label: Required Gender
inputs.help: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

inputs.name: requiredMaxAge
inputs.label: Required Max Age
inputs.help: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

inputs.name: requiredMinAge
inputs.label: Required Min Age
inputs.help: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

inputs.name: suggestedAge
inputs.label: Suggested Age
inputs.help: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

inputs.name: suggestedGender
inputs.label: Suggested Gender
inputs.help: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

inputs.name: suggestedMaxAge
inputs.label: Suggested Max Age
inputs.help: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

inputs.name: suggestedMeasurement
inputs.label: Suggested Measurement
inputs.help: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

inputs.name: suggestedMinAge
inputs.label: Suggested Min Age
inputs.help: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

SportsOrganization.name: SportsOrganization
SportsOrganization.help: Represents the collection of all sports organizations, including sports teams, governing bodies, and sports associations.

inputs.name: sport
inputs.label: Sport
inputs.help: A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

MedicalGuidelineRecommendation.name: MedicalGuidelineRecommendation
MedicalGuidelineRecommendation.help: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

inputs.name: recommendationStrength
inputs.label: Recommendation Strength
inputs.help: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

inputs.name: availableService
inputs.label: Available Service
inputs.help: A medical service available from this provider.

inputs.name: healthcareReportingData
inputs.label: Healthcare Reporting Data
inputs.help: Indicates data describing a hospital, e.g. a CDC [[CDCPMDRecord]] or as some kind of [[Dataset]].

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.label: Medical Specialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

DriveWheelConfigurationValue.name: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
DriveWheelConfigurationValue.help: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

ReportageNewsArticle.name: ReportageNewsArticle
ReportageNewsArticle.help:
The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is a subtype of [[NewsArticle]] representing
 news articles which are the result of journalistic news reporting conventions.

In practice many news publishers produce a wide variety of article types, many of which might be considered a [[NewsArticle]] but not a [[ReportageNewsArticle]]. For example, opinion pieces, reviews, analysis, sponsored or satirical articles, or articles that combine several of these elements.

The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is based on a stricter ideal for "news" as a work of journalism, with articles based on factual information either observed or verified by the author, or reported and verified from knowledgeable sources.  This often includes perspectives from multiple viewpoints on a particular issue (distinguishing news reports from public relations or propaganda).  News reports in the [[ReportageNewsArticle]] sense de-emphasize the opinion of the author, with commentary and value judgements typically expressed elsewhere.

A [[ReportageNewsArticle]] which goes deeper into analysis can also be marked with an additional type of [[AnalysisNewsArticle]].

SeaBodyOfWater.name: SeaBodyOfWater
SeaBodyOfWater.help: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

HotelRoom.name: HotelRoom
HotelRoom.help:
A hotel room is a single room in a hotel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

inputs.name: bed
inputs.label: Bed
inputs.help:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

inputs.name: occupancy
inputs.label: Occupancy
inputs.help:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person.

HowTo.name: HowTo
HowTo.help: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.

inputs.name: estimatedCost
inputs.label: Estimated Cost
inputs.help: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

inputs.name: performTime
inputs.label: Perform Time
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: prepTime
inputs.label: Prep Time
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: step
inputs.label: Step
inputs.help: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

inputs.name: steps
inputs.label: Steps
inputs.help: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

inputs.name: supply
inputs.label: Supply
inputs.help: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: tool
inputs.label: Tool
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: totalTime
inputs.label: Total Time
inputs.help: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: yield
inputs.label: Yield
inputs.help: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

DrugCostCategory.name: DrugCostCategory
DrugCostCategory.help: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

IgnoreAction.name: IgnoreAction
IgnoreAction.help: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

WorkBasedProgram.name: WorkBasedProgram
WorkBasedProgram.help: A program with both an educational and employment component. Typically based at a workplace and structured around work-based learning, with the aim of instilling competencies related to an occupation. WorkBasedProgram is used to distinguish programs such as apprenticeships from school, college or other classroom based educational programs.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.label: Occupational Category
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: trainingSalary
inputs.label: Training Salary
inputs.help: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

MedicalTestPanel.name: MedicalTestPanel
MedicalTestPanel.help: Any collection of tests commonly ordered together.

inputs.name: subTest
inputs.label: Sub Test
inputs.help: A component test of the panel.

RadioBroadcastService.name: RadioBroadcastService
RadioBroadcastService.help: A delivery service through which radio content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

EventReservation.name: EventReservation
EventReservation.help: A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

Recommendation.name: Recommendation
Recommendation.help: [[Recommendation]] is a type of [[Review]] that suggests or proposes something as the best option or best course of action. Recommendations may be for products or services, or other concrete things, as in the case of a ranked list or product guide. A [[Guide]] may list multiple recommendations for different categories. For example, in a [[Guide]] about which TVs to buy, the author may have several [[Recommendation]]s.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

PhysicalActivity.name: PhysicalActivity
PhysicalActivity.help: Any bodily activity that enhances or maintains physical fitness and overall health and wellness. Includes activity that is part of daily living and routine, structured exercise, and exercise prescribed as part of a medical treatment or recovery plan.

inputs.name: associatedAnatomy
inputs.label: Associated Anatomy
inputs.help: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: epidemiology
inputs.label: Epidemiology
inputs.help: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

inputs.name: pathophysiology
inputs.label: Pathophysiology
inputs.help: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

inputs.name: numberOfAccommodationUnits
inputs.label: Number Of Accommodation Units
inputs.help: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

inputs.name: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
inputs.label: Number Of Available Accommodation Units
inputs.help: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

inputs.name: numberOfBedrooms
inputs.label: Number Of Bedrooms
inputs.help: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

inputs.name: petsAllowed
inputs.label: Pets Allowed
inputs.help: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

inputs.name: tourBookingPage
inputs.label: Tour Booking Page
inputs.help: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

BusOrCoach.name: BusOrCoach
BusOrCoach.help: A bus (also omnibus or autobus) is a road vehicle designed to carry passengers. Coaches are luxury buses, usually in service for long distance travel.

inputs.name: acrissCode
inputs.label: Acriss Code
inputs.help: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

inputs.name: roofLoad
inputs.label: Roof Load
inputs.help:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

MusicGroup.name: MusicGroup
MusicGroup.help: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

inputs.name: album
inputs.label: Album
inputs.help: A music album.

inputs.name: albums
inputs.label: Albums
inputs.help: A collection of music albums.

inputs.name: genre
inputs.label: Genre
inputs.help: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

inputs.name: musicGroupMember
inputs.label: Music Group Member
inputs.help: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

inputs.name: track
inputs.label: Track
inputs.help: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

inputs.name: tracks
inputs.label: Tracks
inputs.help: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

EatAction.name: EatAction
EatAction.help: The act of swallowing solid objects.

PathologyTest.name: PathologyTest
PathologyTest.help: A medical test performed by a laboratory that typically involves examination of a tissue sample by a pathologist.

inputs.name: tissueSample
inputs.label: Tissue Sample
inputs.help: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

LiquorStore.name: LiquorStore
LiquorStore.help: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

GovernmentService.name: GovernmentService
GovernmentService.help: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

inputs.name: jurisdiction
inputs.label: Jurisdiction
inputs.help: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

inputs.name: serviceOperator
inputs.label: Service Operator
inputs.help: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

BankAccount.name: BankAccount
BankAccount.help: A product or service offered by a bank whereby one may deposit, withdraw or transfer money and in some cases be paid interest.

inputs.name: accountMinimumInflow
inputs.label: Account Minimum Inflow
inputs.help: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

inputs.name: accountOverdraftLimit
inputs.label: Account Overdraft Limit
inputs.help: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

inputs.name: bankAccountType
inputs.label: Bank Account Type
inputs.help: The type of a bank account.

MedicalImagingTechnique.name: MedicalImagingTechnique
MedicalImagingTechnique.help: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

QuantitativeValue.name: QuantitativeValue
QuantitativeValue.help: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

inputs.name: additionalProperty
inputs.label: Additional Property
inputs.help: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

inputs.name: maxValue
inputs.label: Max Value
inputs.help: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: minValue
inputs.label: Min Value
inputs.help: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: unitCode
inputs.label: Unit Code
inputs.help: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

inputs.name: unitText
inputs.label: Unit Text
inputs.help: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

inputs.name: value
inputs.label: Value
inputs.help:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: valueReference
inputs.label: Value Reference
inputs.help: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

inputs.name: caption
inputs.label: Caption
inputs.help: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

inputs.name: embeddedTextCaption
inputs.label: Embedded Text Caption
inputs.help: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

inputs.name: transcript
inputs.label: Transcript
inputs.help: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

GeoCoordinates.name: GeoCoordinates
GeoCoordinates.help: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

inputs.name: address
inputs.label: Address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: addressCountry
inputs.label: Address Country
inputs.help: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

inputs.name: elevation
inputs.label: Elevation
inputs.help: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

inputs.name: latitude
inputs.label: Latitude
inputs.help: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

inputs.name: longitude
inputs.label: Longitude
inputs.help: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

inputs.name: postalCode
inputs.label: Postal Code
inputs.help: The postal code. For example, 94043.

WPAdBlock.name: WPAdBlock
WPAdBlock.help: An advertising section of the page.

AgreeAction.name: AgreeAction
AgreeAction.help: The act of expressing a consistency of opinion with the object. An agent agrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

Residence.name: Residence
Residence.help: The place where a person lives.

inputs.name: accommodationFloorPlan
inputs.label: Accommodation Floor Plan
inputs.help: A floorplan of some [[Accommodation]].

MedicalTest.name: MedicalTest
MedicalTest.help: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

inputs.name: affectedBy
inputs.label: Affected By
inputs.help: Drugs that affect the test's results.

inputs.name: normalRange
inputs.label: Normal Range
inputs.help: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

inputs.name: signDetected
inputs.label: Sign Detected
inputs.help: A sign detected by the test.

inputs.name: usedToDiagnose
inputs.label: Used To Diagnose
inputs.help: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

inputs.name: usesDevice
inputs.label: Uses Device
inputs.help: Device used to perform the test.

Drawing.name: Drawing
Drawing.help: A picture or diagram made with a pencil, pen, or crayon rather than paint.

EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.name: EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.help: Enumerates the EU energy efficiency classes A-G as well as A+, A++, and A+++ as defined in EU directive 2017/1369.

Question.name: Question
Question.help: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

inputs.name: acceptedAnswer
inputs.label: Accepted Answer
inputs.help: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

inputs.name: answerCount
inputs.label: Answer Count
inputs.help: The number of answers this question has received.

inputs.name: eduQuestionType
inputs.label: Edu Question Type
inputs.help: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

inputs.name: parentItem
inputs.label: Parent Item
inputs.help: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

inputs.name: suggestedAnswer
inputs.label: Suggested Answer
inputs.help: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

MedicalCondition.name: MedicalCondition
MedicalCondition.help: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

inputs.name: associatedAnatomy
inputs.label: Associated Anatomy
inputs.help: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

inputs.name: differentialDiagnosis
inputs.label: Differential Diagnosis
inputs.help: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

inputs.name: drug
inputs.label: Drug
inputs.help: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

inputs.name: epidemiology
inputs.label: Epidemiology
inputs.help: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

inputs.name: expectedPrognosis
inputs.label: Expected Prognosis
inputs.help: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

inputs.name: naturalProgression
inputs.label: Natural Progression
inputs.help: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

inputs.name: pathophysiology
inputs.label: Pathophysiology
inputs.help: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

inputs.name: possibleComplication
inputs.label: Possible Complication
inputs.help: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

inputs.name: possibleTreatment
inputs.label: Possible Treatment
inputs.help: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

inputs.name: primaryPrevention
inputs.label: Primary Prevention
inputs.help: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

inputs.name: riskFactor
inputs.label: Risk Factor
inputs.help: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

inputs.name: secondaryPrevention
inputs.label: Secondary Prevention
inputs.help: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

inputs.name: signOrSymptom
inputs.label: Sign Or Symptom
inputs.help: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

inputs.name: stage
inputs.label: Stage
inputs.help: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

inputs.name: status
inputs.label: Status
inputs.help: The status of the study (enumerated).

inputs.name: typicalTest
inputs.label: Typical Test
inputs.help: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

ArchiveComponent.name: ArchiveComponent
ArchiveComponent.help: An intangible type to be applied to any archive content, carrying with it a set of properties required to describe archival items and collections.

inputs.name: holdingArchive
inputs.label: Holding Archive
inputs.help: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

inputs.name: itemLocation
inputs.label: Item Location
inputs.help: Current location of the item.

Clip.name: Clip
Clip.help: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.label: Actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.label: Actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: clipNumber
inputs.label: Clip Number
inputs.help: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

inputs.name: director
inputs.label: Director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.label: Directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: endOffset
inputs.label: End Offset
inputs.help: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.label: Music By
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: partOfEpisode
inputs.label: Part Of Episode
inputs.help: The episode to which this clip belongs.

inputs.name: partOfSeason
inputs.label: Part Of Season
inputs.help: The season to which this episode belongs.

inputs.name: partOfSeries
inputs.label: Part Of Series
inputs.help: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

inputs.name: startOffset
inputs.label: Start Offset
inputs.help: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

WebPageElement.name: WebPageElement
WebPageElement.help: A web page element, like a table or an image.

inputs.name: cssSelector
inputs.label: Css Selector
inputs.help: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

inputs.name: xpath
inputs.label: Xpath
inputs.help: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

PriceTypeEnumeration.name: PriceTypeEnumeration
PriceTypeEnumeration.help: Enumerates different price types, for example list price, invoice price, and sale price.

BusReservation.name: BusReservation
BusReservation.help: A reservation for bus travel. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

EventStatusType.name: EventStatusType
EventStatusType.help: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

MediaEnumeration.name: MediaEnumeration
MediaEnumeration.help: MediaEnumeration enumerations are lists of codes, labels etc. useful for describing media objects. They may be reflections of externally developed lists, or created at schema.org, or a combination.

QuoteAction.name: QuoteAction
QuoteAction.help: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

WebSite.name: WebSite
WebSite.help: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

inputs.name: issn
inputs.label: Issn
inputs.help: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

Enumeration.name: Enumeration
Enumeration.help: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

inputs.name: supersededBy
inputs.label: Superseded By
inputs.help: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

TransferAction.name: TransferAction
TransferAction.help: The act of transferring/moving (abstract or concrete) animate or inanimate objects from one place to another.

inputs.name: fromLocation
inputs.label: From Location
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

inputs.name: toLocation
inputs.label: To Location
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

PlayGameAction.name: PlayGameAction
PlayGameAction.help: The act of playing a video game.

inputs.name: gameAvailabilityType
inputs.label: Game Availability Type
inputs.help: Indicates the availability type of the game content associated with this action, such as whether it is a full version or a demo.

MovieSeries.name: MovieSeries
MovieSeries.help: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.label: Actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.label: Actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: director
inputs.label: Director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.label: Directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.label: Music By
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.label: Production Company
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.label: Trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

ControlAction.name: ControlAction
ControlAction.help: An agent controls a device or application.

ReactAction.name: ReactAction
ReactAction.help: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

DownloadAction.name: DownloadAction
DownloadAction.help: The act of downloading an object.

TechArticle.name: TechArticle
TechArticle.help: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

inputs.name: dependencies
inputs.label: Dependencies
inputs.help: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

inputs.name: proficiencyLevel
inputs.label: Proficiency Level
inputs.help: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

DisagreeAction.name: DisagreeAction
DisagreeAction.help: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

MedicalStudy.name: MedicalStudy
MedicalStudy.help: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, use MedicalScholarlyArticle. Note: use the code property of MedicalEntity to store study IDs, e.g. clinicaltrials.gov ID.

inputs.name: healthCondition
inputs.label: Health Condition
inputs.help: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

inputs.name: sponsor
inputs.label: Sponsor
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

inputs.name: status
inputs.label: Status
inputs.help: The status of the study (enumerated).

inputs.name: studyLocation
inputs.label: Study Location
inputs.help: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

inputs.name: studySubject
inputs.label: Study Subject
inputs.help: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

BroadcastService.name: BroadcastService
BroadcastService.help: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

inputs.name: area
inputs.label: Area
inputs.help: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

inputs.name: broadcastAffiliateOf
inputs.label: Broadcast Affiliate Of
inputs.help: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

inputs.name: broadcastDisplayName
inputs.label: Broadcast Display Name
inputs.help: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

inputs.name: broadcastFrequency
inputs.label: Broadcast Frequency
inputs.help: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

inputs.name: broadcastTimezone
inputs.label: Broadcast Timezone
inputs.help: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

inputs.name: broadcaster
inputs.label: Broadcaster
inputs.help: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

inputs.name: callSign
inputs.label: Call Sign
inputs.help: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

inputs.name: hasBroadcastChannel
inputs.label: Has Broadcast Channel
inputs.help: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

inputs.name: inLanguage
inputs.label: In Language
inputs.help: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

inputs.name: parentService
inputs.label: Parent Service
inputs.help: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

inputs.name: videoFormat
inputs.label: Video Format
inputs.help: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

PhysicalExam.name: PhysicalExam
PhysicalExam.help: A type of physical examination of a patient performed by a physician.

Review.name: Review
Review.help: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

inputs.name: associatedClaimReview
inputs.label: Associated Claim Review
inputs.help: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

inputs.name: associatedMediaReview
inputs.label: Associated Media Review
inputs.help: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

inputs.name: associatedReview
inputs.label: Associated Review
inputs.help: An associated [[Review]].

inputs.name: itemReviewed
inputs.label: Item Reviewed
inputs.help: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

inputs.name: negativeNotes
inputs.label: Negative Notes
inputs.help:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]].

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

inputs.name: positiveNotes
inputs.label: Positive Notes
inputs.help:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.
