In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.label: Review Aspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

inputs.name: reviewBody
inputs.label: Review Body
inputs.help: The actual body of the review.

inputs.name: reviewRating
inputs.label: Review Rating
inputs.help: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

PsychologicalTreatment.name: PsychologicalTreatment
PsychologicalTreatment.help: A process of care relying upon counseling, dialogue and communication  aimed at improving a mental health condition without use of drugs.

UnRegisterAction.name: UnRegisterAction
UnRegisterAction.help:
The act of un-registering from a service.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: antonym of UnRegisterAction.
* [[LeaveAction]]: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you were previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people.

State.name: State
State.help: A state or province of a country.

ResumeAction.name: ResumeAction
ResumeAction.help: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

ServiceChannel.name: ServiceChannel
ServiceChannel.help: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

inputs.name: availableLanguage
inputs.label: Available Language
inputs.help: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

inputs.name: processingTime
inputs.label: Processing Time
inputs.help: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

inputs.name: providesService
inputs.label: Provides Service
inputs.help: The service provided by this channel.

inputs.name: serviceLocation
inputs.label: Service Location
inputs.help: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

inputs.name: servicePhone
inputs.label: Service Phone
inputs.help: The phone number to use to access the service.

inputs.name: servicePostalAddress
inputs.label: Service Postal Address
inputs.help: The address for accessing the service by mail.

inputs.name: serviceSmsNumber
inputs.label: Service Sms Number
inputs.help: The number to access the service by text message.

inputs.name: serviceUrl
inputs.label: Service Url
inputs.help: The website to access the service.

VisualArtwork.name: VisualArtwork
VisualArtwork.help: A work of art that is primarily visual in character.

inputs.name: artEdition
inputs.label: Art Edition
inputs.help: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

inputs.name: artMedium
inputs.label: Art Medium
inputs.help: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

inputs.name: artform
inputs.label: Artform
inputs.help: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

inputs.name: artist
inputs.label: Artist
inputs.help:
The primary artist for a work
    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

inputs.name: artworkSurface
inputs.label: Artwork Surface
inputs.help: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

inputs.name: colorist
inputs.label: Colorist
inputs.help: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

inputs.name: depth
inputs.label: Depth
inputs.help: The depth of the item.

inputs.name: height
inputs.label: Height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: inker
inputs.label: Inker
inputs.help: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

inputs.name: letterer
inputs.label: Letterer
inputs.help: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

inputs.name: penciler
inputs.label: Penciler
inputs.help: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

inputs.name: surface
inputs.label: Surface
inputs.help: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

inputs.name: width
inputs.label: Width
inputs.help: The width of the item.

EducationalOccupationalProgram.name: EducationalOccupationalProgram
EducationalOccupationalProgram.help: A program offered by an institution which determines the learning progress to achieve an outcome, usually a credential like a degree or certificate. This would define a discrete set of opportunities (e.g., job, courses) that together constitute a program with a clear start, end, set of requirements, and transition to a new occupational opportunity (e.g., a job), or sometimes a higher educational opportunity (e.g., an advanced degree).

inputs.name: applicationDeadline
inputs.label: Application Deadline
inputs.help: The date at which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

inputs.name: applicationStartDate
inputs.label: Application Start Date
inputs.help: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

inputs.name: dayOfWeek
inputs.label: Day Of Week
inputs.help: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

inputs.name: educationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.label: Educational Credential Awarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

inputs.name: educationalProgramMode
inputs.label: Educational Program Mode
inputs.help: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

inputs.name: endDate
inputs.label: End Date
inputs.help: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: financialAidEligible
inputs.label: Financial Aid Eligible
inputs.help: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

inputs.name: hasCourse
inputs.label: Has Course
inputs.help: A course or class that is one of the learning opportunities that constitute an educational / occupational program. No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

inputs.name: maximumEnrollment
inputs.label: Maximum Enrollment
inputs.help: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

inputs.name: numberOfCredits
inputs.label: Number Of Credits
inputs.help: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.label: Occupational Category
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: occupationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.label: Occupational Credential Awarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

inputs.name: offers
inputs.label: Offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: programPrerequisites
inputs.label: Program Prerequisites
inputs.help: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

inputs.name: programType
inputs.label: Program Type
inputs.help: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.label: Provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: salaryUponCompletion
inputs.label: Salary Upon Completion
inputs.help: The expected salary upon completing the training.

inputs.name: startDate
inputs.label: Start Date
inputs.help: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: termDuration
inputs.label: Term Duration
inputs.help: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

inputs.name: termsPerYear
inputs.label: Terms Per Year
inputs.help: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

inputs.name: timeOfDay
inputs.label: Time Of Day
inputs.help: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

inputs.name: timeToComplete
inputs.label: Time To Complete
inputs.help: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

inputs.name: trainingSalary
inputs.label: Training Salary
inputs.help: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

inputs.name: typicalCreditsPerTerm
inputs.label: Typical Credits Per Term
inputs.help: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

Thesis.name: Thesis
Thesis.help: A thesis or dissertation document submitted in support of candidature for an academic degree or professional qualification.

inputs.name: inSupportOf
inputs.label: In Support Of
inputs.help: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

ViewAction.name: ViewAction
ViewAction.help: The act of consuming static visual content.

LymphaticVessel.name: LymphaticVessel
LymphaticVessel.help: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries lymph fluid unidirectionally toward the heart.

inputs.name: originatesFrom
inputs.label: Originates From
inputs.help: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

inputs.name: regionDrained
inputs.label: Region Drained
inputs.help: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

inputs.name: runsTo
inputs.label: Runs To
inputs.help: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

DefinedRegion.name: DefinedRegion
DefinedRegion.help:
A DefinedRegion is a geographic area defined by potentially arbitrary (rather than political, administrative or natural geographical) criteria. Properties are provided for defining a region by reference to sets of postal codes.

Examples: a delivery destination when shopping. Region where regional pricing is configured.

Requirement 1:
Country: US
States: "NY", "CA"

Requirement 2:
Country: US
PostalCode Set: { [94000-94585], [97000, 97999], [13000, 13599]}
{ [12345, 12345], [78945, 78945], }
Region = state, canton, prefecture, autonomous community...

inputs.name: addressCountry
inputs.label: Address Country
inputs.help: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

inputs.name: addressRegion
inputs.label: Address Region
inputs.help: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

inputs.name: postalCode
inputs.label: Postal Code
inputs.help: The postal code. For example, 94043.

inputs.name: postalCodePrefix
inputs.label: Postal Code Prefix
inputs.help: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

inputs.name: postalCodeRange
inputs.label: Postal Code Range
inputs.help: A defined range of postal codes.

3DModel.name: 3DModel
3DModel.help:
A 3D model represents some kind of 3D content, which may have [[encoding]]s in one or more [[MediaObject]]s. Many 3D formats are available (e.g. see [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:3D_graphics_file_formats)); specific encoding formats can be represented using the [[encodingFormat]] property applied to the relevant [[MediaObject]]. For the
case of a single file published after Zip compression, the convention of appending '+zip' to the [[encodingFormat]] can be used. Geospatial, AR/VR, artistic/animation, gaming, engineering and scientific content can all be represented using [[3DModel]].

inputs.name: isResizable
inputs.label: Is Resizable
inputs.help: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

WinAction.name: WinAction
WinAction.help: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

inputs.name: loser
inputs.label: Loser
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

MapCategoryType.name: MapCategoryType
MapCategoryType.help: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

MeetingRoom.name: MeetingRoom
MeetingRoom.help:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

StatisticalVariable.name: StatisticalVariable
StatisticalVariable.help: [[StatisticalVariable]] represents any type of statistical metric that can be measured at a place and time. The usage pattern for [[StatisticalVariable]] is typically expressed using [[Observation]] with an explicit [[populationType]], which is a type, typically drawn from Schema.org. Each [[StatisticalVariable]] is marked as a [[ConstraintNode]], meaning that some properties (those listed using [[constraintProperty]]) serve in this setting solely to define the statistical variable rather than literally describe a specific person, place or thing. For example, a [[StatisticalVariable]] Median_Height_Person_Female representing the median height of women, could be written as follows: the population type is [[Person]]; the measuredProperty [[height]]; the [[statType]] [[median]]; the [[gender]] [[Female]]. It is important to note that there are many kinds of scientific quantitative observation which are not fully, perfectly or unambiguously described following this pattern, or with solely Schema.org terminology. The approach taken here is designed to allow partial, incremental or minimal description of [[StatisticalVariable]]s, and the use of detailed sets of entity and property IDs from external repositories. The [[measurementMethod]], [[unitCode]] and [[unitText]] properties can also be used to clarify the specific nature and notation of an observed measurement.

inputs.name: measuredProperty
inputs.label: Measured Property
inputs.help: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], typically via its [[StatisticalVariable]]. There are various kinds of applicable [[Property]]: a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, Data Commons, Wikidata, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

inputs.name: measurementDenominator
inputs.label: Measurement Denominator
inputs.help: Identifies the denominator variable when an observation represents a ratio or percentage.

inputs.name: measurementMethod
inputs.label: Measurement Method
inputs.help: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

inputs.name: measurementQualifier
inputs.label: Measurement Qualifier
inputs.help: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.label: Measurement Technique
inputs.help:
A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable.
    
The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. 

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". 

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

inputs.name: populationType
inputs.label: Population Type
inputs.help: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

inputs.name: statType
inputs.label: Stat Type
inputs.help: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[count]], [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

GeoCircle.name: GeoCircle
GeoCircle.help:
A GeoCircle is a GeoShape representing a circular geographic area. As it is a GeoShape
          it provides the simple textual property 'circle', but also allows the combination of postalCode alongside geoRadius.
          The center of the circle can be indicated via the 'geoMidpoint' property, or more approximately using 'address', 'postalCode'.

inputs.name: geoMidpoint
inputs.label: Geo Midpoint
inputs.help: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

inputs.name: geoRadius
inputs.label: Geo Radius
inputs.help: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

Atlas.name: Atlas
Atlas.help: A collection or bound volume of maps, charts, plates or tables, physical or in media form illustrating any subject.

PhysicalActivityCategory.name: PhysicalActivityCategory
PhysicalActivityCategory.help: Categories of physical activity, organized by physiologic classification.

CommentAction.name: CommentAction
CommentAction.help: The act of generating a comment about a subject.

inputs.name: resultComment
inputs.label: Result Comment
inputs.help: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

PayAction.name: PayAction
PayAction.help: An agent pays a price to a participant.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.label: Recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

JobPosting.name: JobPosting
JobPosting.help: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

inputs.name: applicantLocationRequirements
inputs.label: Applicant Location Requirements
inputs.help: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

inputs.name: applicationContact
inputs.label: Application Contact
inputs.help: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

inputs.name: baseSalary
inputs.label: Base Salary
inputs.help: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

inputs.name: benefits
inputs.label: Benefits
inputs.help: Description of benefits associated with the job.

inputs.name: datePosted
inputs.label: Date Posted
inputs.help: Publication date of an online listing.

inputs.name: directApply
inputs.label: Direct Apply
inputs.help: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

inputs.name: educationRequirements
inputs.label: Education Requirements
inputs.help: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
inputs.label: Eligibility To Work Requirement
inputs.help: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

inputs.name: employerOverview
inputs.label: Employer Overview
inputs.help: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

inputs.name: employmentType
inputs.label: Employment Type
inputs.help: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

inputs.name: employmentUnit
inputs.label: Employment Unit
inputs.help: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

inputs.name: estimatedSalary
inputs.label: Estimated Salary
inputs.help: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

inputs.name: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
inputs.label: Experience In Place Of Education
inputs.help: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

inputs.name: experienceRequirements
inputs.label: Experience Requirements
inputs.help: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: hiringOrganization
inputs.label: Hiring Organization
inputs.help: Organization or Person offering the job position.

inputs.name: incentiveCompensation
inputs.label: Incentive Compensation
inputs.help: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

inputs.name: incentives
inputs.label: Incentives
inputs.help: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

inputs.name: industry
inputs.label: Industry
inputs.help: The industry associated with the job position.

inputs.name: jobBenefits
inputs.label: Job Benefits
inputs.help: Description of benefits associated with the job.

inputs.name: jobImmediateStart
inputs.label: Job Immediate Start
inputs.help: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

inputs.name: jobLocation
inputs.label: Job Location
inputs.help: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

inputs.name: jobLocationType
inputs.label: Job Location Type
inputs.help: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

inputs.name: jobStartDate
inputs.label: Job Start Date
inputs.help: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.label: Occupational Category
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: physicalRequirement
inputs.label: Physical Requirement
inputs.help: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

inputs.name: qualifications
inputs.label: Qualifications
inputs.help: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: relevantOccupation
inputs.label: Relevant Occupation
inputs.help: The Occupation for the JobPosting.

inputs.name: responsibilities
inputs.label: Responsibilities
inputs.help: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: salaryCurrency
inputs.label: Salary Currency
inputs.help: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

inputs.name: securityClearanceRequirement
inputs.label: Security Clearance Requirement
inputs.help: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

inputs.name: sensoryRequirement
inputs.label: Sensory Requirement
inputs.help: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

inputs.name: skills
inputs.label: Skills
inputs.help: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

inputs.name: specialCommitments
inputs.label: Special Commitments
inputs.help: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

inputs.name: title
inputs.label: Title
inputs.help: The title of the job.

inputs.name: totalJobOpenings
inputs.label: Total Job Openings
inputs.help: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.label: Valid Through
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: workHours
inputs.label: Work Hours
inputs.help: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

LocalBusiness.name: LocalBusiness
LocalBusiness.help: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

inputs.name: branchOf
inputs.label: Branch Of
inputs.help: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].

inputs.name: currenciesAccepted
inputs.label: Currencies Accepted
inputs.help: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: openingHours
inputs.label: Opening Hours
inputs.help: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

inputs.name: paymentAccepted
inputs.label: Payment Accepted
inputs.help: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

inputs.name: priceRange
inputs.label: Price Range
inputs.help: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

Organization.name: Organization
Organization.help: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

inputs.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
inputs.label: Accepted Payment Method
inputs.help: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

inputs.name: actionableFeedbackPolicy
inputs.label: Actionable Feedback Policy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

inputs.name: address
inputs.label: Address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: agentInteractionStatistic
inputs.label: Agent Interaction Statistic
inputs.help: The number of completed interactions for this entity, in a particular role (the 'agent'), in a particular action (indicated in the statistic), and in a particular context (i.e. interactionService).

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: alumni
inputs.label: Alumni
inputs.help: Alumni of an organization.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.label: Area Served
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: award
inputs.label: Award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: awards
inputs.label: Awards
inputs.help: Awards won by or for this item.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.label: Brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: contactPoint
inputs.label: Contact Point
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: contactPoints
inputs.label: Contact Points
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: correctionsPolicy
inputs.label: Corrections Policy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

inputs.name: department
inputs.label: Department
inputs.help: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

inputs.name: dissolutionDate
inputs.label: Dissolution Date
inputs.help: The date that this organization was dissolved.

inputs.name: diversityPolicy
inputs.label: Diversity Policy
inputs.help: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

inputs.name: diversityStaffingReport
inputs.label: Diversity Staffing Report
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

inputs.name: duns
inputs.label: Duns
inputs.help: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

inputs.name: email
inputs.label: Email
inputs.help: Email address.

inputs.name: employee
inputs.label: Employee
inputs.help: Someone working for this organization.

inputs.name: employees
inputs.label: Employees
inputs.help: People working for this organization.

inputs.name: ethicsPolicy
inputs.label: Ethics Policy
inputs.help: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

inputs.name: event
inputs.label: Event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

inputs.name: events
inputs.label: Events
inputs.help: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

inputs.name: faxNumber
inputs.label: Fax Number
inputs.help: The fax number.

inputs.name: founder
inputs.label: Founder
inputs.help: A person who founded this organization.

inputs.name: founders
inputs.label: Founders
inputs.help: A person who founded this organization.

inputs.name: foundingDate
inputs.label: Founding Date
inputs.help: The date that this organization was founded.

inputs.name: foundingLocation
inputs.label: Founding Location
inputs.help: The place where the Organization was founded.

inputs.name: funder
inputs.label: Funder
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

inputs.name: funding
inputs.label: Funding
inputs.help: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

inputs.name: globalLocationNumber
inputs.label: Global Location Number
inputs.help: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

inputs.name: hasCertification
inputs.label: Has Certification
inputs.help: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

inputs.name: hasCredential
inputs.label: Has Credential
inputs.help: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

inputs.name: hasGS1DigitalLink
inputs.label: Has GS 1 Digital Link
inputs.help:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

inputs.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
inputs.label: Has Merchant Return Policy
inputs.help: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

inputs.name: hasOfferCatalog
inputs.label: Has Offer Catalog
inputs.help: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

inputs.name: hasPOS
inputs.label: Has POS
inputs.help: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

inputs.name: interactionStatistic
inputs.label: Interaction Statistic
inputs.help: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

inputs.name: isicV4
inputs.label: Isic V 4
inputs.help: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

inputs.name: iso6523Code
inputs.label: Iso 6523 Code
inputs.help: An organization identifier as defined in [ISO 6523(-1)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_6523). The identifier should be in the `XXXX:YYYYYY:ZZZ` or `XXXX:YYYYYY`format. Where `XXXX` is a 4 digit _ICD_ (International Code Designator), `YYYYYY` is an _OID_ (Organization Identifier) with all formatting characters (dots, dashes, spaces) removed with a maximal length of 35 characters, and `ZZZ` is an optional OPI (Organization Part Identifier) with a maximum length of 35 characters. The various components (ICD, OID, OPI) are joined with a colon character (ASCII `0x3a`). Note that many existing organization identifiers defined as attributes like [leiCode](http://schema.org/leiCode) (`0199`), [duns](http://schema.org/duns) (`0060`) or [GLN](http://schema.org/globalLocationNumber) (`0088`) can be expressed using ISO-6523. If possible, ISO-6523 codes should be preferred to populating [vatID](http://schema.org/vatID) or [taxID](http://schema.org/taxID), as ISO identifiers are less ambiguous.

inputs.name: keywords
inputs.label: Keywords
inputs.help: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

inputs.name: knowsAbout
inputs.label: Knows About
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

inputs.name: knowsLanguage
inputs.label: Knows Language
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

inputs.name: legalName
inputs.label: Legal Name
inputs.help: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

inputs.name: leiCode
inputs.label: Lei Code
inputs.help: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

inputs.name: location
inputs.label: Location
inputs.help: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: makesOffer
inputs.label: Makes Offer
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

inputs.name: member
inputs.label: Member
inputs.help: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

inputs.name: memberOf
inputs.label: Member Of
inputs.help: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

inputs.name: members
inputs.label: Members
inputs.help: A member of this organization.

inputs.name: naics
inputs.label: Naics
inputs.help: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

inputs.name: nonprofitStatus
inputs.label: Nonprofit Status
inputs.help: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

inputs.name: numberOfEmployees
inputs.label: Number Of Employees
inputs.help: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

inputs.name: ownershipFundingInfo
inputs.label: Ownership Funding Info
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

inputs.name: owns
inputs.label: Owns
inputs.help: Products owned by the organization or person.

inputs.name: parentOrganization
inputs.label: Parent Organization
inputs.help: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

inputs.name: publishingPrinciples
inputs.label: Publishing Principles
inputs.help:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.label: Reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: seeks
inputs.label: Seeks
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

inputs.name: serviceArea
inputs.label: Service Area
inputs.help: The geographic area where the service is provided.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.label: Slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: sponsor
inputs.label: Sponsor
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

inputs.name: subOrganization
inputs.label: Sub Organization
inputs.help: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

inputs.name: taxID
inputs.label: Tax ID
inputs.help: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

inputs.name: telephone
inputs.label: Telephone
inputs.help: The telephone number.

inputs.name: unnamedSourcesPolicy
inputs.label: Unnamed Sources Policy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

inputs.name: vatID
inputs.label: Vat ID
inputs.help: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

AssignAction.name: AssignAction
AssignAction.help: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

GameServer.name: GameServer
GameServer.help: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

inputs.name: game
inputs.label: Game
inputs.help: Video game which is played on this server.

inputs.name: playersOnline
inputs.label: Players Online
inputs.help: Number of players on the server.

inputs.name: serverStatus
inputs.label: Server Status
inputs.help: Status of a game server.

ShortStory.name: ShortStory
ShortStory.help: Short story or tale. A brief work of literature, usually written in narrative prose.

SuperficialAnatomy.name: SuperficialAnatomy
SuperficialAnatomy.help: Anatomical features that can be observed by sight (without dissection), including the form and proportions of the human body as well as surface landmarks that correspond to deeper subcutaneous structures. Superficial anatomy plays an important role in sports medicine, phlebotomy, and other medical specialties as underlying anatomical structures can be identified through surface palpation. For example, during back surgery, superficial anatomy can be used to palpate and count vertebrae to find the site of incision. Or in phlebotomy, superficial anatomy can be used to locate an underlying vein; for example, the median cubital vein can be located by palpating the borders of the cubital fossa (such as the epicondyles of the humerus) and then looking for the superficial signs of the vein, such as size, prominence, ability to refill after depression, and feel of surrounding tissue support. As another example, in a subluxation (dislocation) of the glenohumeral joint, the bony structure becomes pronounced with the deltoid muscle failing to cover the glenohumeral joint allowing the edges of the scapula to be superficially visible. Here, the superficial anatomy is the visible edges of the scapula, implying the underlying dislocation of the joint (the related anatomical structure).

inputs.name: associatedPathophysiology
inputs.label: Associated Pathophysiology
inputs.help: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

inputs.name: relatedAnatomy
inputs.label: Related Anatomy
inputs.help: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

inputs.name: relatedCondition
inputs.label: Related Condition
inputs.help: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

inputs.name: relatedTherapy
inputs.label: Related Therapy
inputs.help: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

inputs.name: significance
inputs.label: Significance
inputs.help: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

ProductCollection.name: ProductCollection
ProductCollection.help: A set of products (either [[ProductGroup]]s or specific variants) that are listed together e.g. in an [[Offer]].

inputs.name: includesObject
inputs.label: Includes Object
inputs.help: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

inputs.name: foodEstablishment
inputs.label: Food Establishment
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

inputs.name: foodEvent
inputs.label: Food Event
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

inputs.name: recipe
inputs.label: Recipe
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

DepartAction.name: DepartAction
DepartAction.help: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from a fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

Blog.name: Blog
Blog.help: A [blog](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blog), sometimes known as a "weblog". Note that the individual posts ([[BlogPosting]]s) in a [[Blog]] are often colloquially referred to by the same term.

inputs.name: blogPost
inputs.label: Blog Post
inputs.help: A posting that is part of this blog.

inputs.name: blogPosts
inputs.label: Blog Posts
inputs.help: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

inputs.name: issn
inputs.label: Issn
inputs.help: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

AnatomicalSystem.name: AnatomicalSystem
AnatomicalSystem.help: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can include circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

inputs.name: associatedPathophysiology
inputs.label: Associated Pathophysiology
inputs.help: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

inputs.name: comprisedOf
inputs.label: Comprised Of
inputs.help: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

inputs.name: relatedCondition
inputs.label: Related Condition
inputs.help: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

inputs.name: relatedStructure
inputs.label: Related Structure
inputs.help: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

inputs.name: relatedTherapy
inputs.label: Related Therapy
inputs.help: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

LiveBlogPosting.name: LiveBlogPosting
LiveBlogPosting.help: A [[LiveBlogPosting]] is a [[BlogPosting]] intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

inputs.name: coverageEndTime
inputs.label: Coverage End Time
inputs.help: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

inputs.name: coverageStartTime
inputs.label: Coverage Start Time
inputs.help: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

inputs.name: liveBlogUpdate
inputs.label: Live Blog Update
inputs.help: An update to the LiveBlog.

BroadcastChannel.name: BroadcastChannel
BroadcastChannel.help: A unique instance of a BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

inputs.name: broadcastChannelId
inputs.label: Broadcast Channel Id
inputs.help: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

inputs.name: broadcastFrequency
inputs.label: Broadcast Frequency
inputs.help: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

inputs.name: broadcastServiceTier
inputs.label: Broadcast Service Tier
inputs.help: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

inputs.name: genre
inputs.label: Genre
inputs.help: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

inputs.name: inBroadcastLineup
inputs.label: In Broadcast Lineup
inputs.help: The CableOrSatelliteService offering the channel.

inputs.name: providesBroadcastService
inputs.label: Provides Broadcast Service
inputs.help: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

UserReview.name: UserReview
UserReview.help: A review created by an end-user (e.g. consumer, purchaser, attendee etc.), in contrast with [[CriticReview]].

DonateAction.name: DonateAction
DonateAction.help: The act of providing goods, services, or money without compensation, often for philanthropic reasons.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.label: Recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

WPFooter.name: WPFooter
WPFooter.help: The footer section of the page.

MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration.name: MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration
MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration.help: Codes for use with the [[mediaAuthenticityCategory]] property, indicating the authenticity of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared). In general these codes are not mutually exclusive, although some combinations (such as 'original' versus 'transformed', 'edited' and 'staged') would be contradictory if applied in the same [[MediaReview]]. Note that the application of these codes is with regard to a piece of media shared or published in a particular context.

Poster.name: Poster
Poster.help: A large, usually printed placard, bill, or announcement, often illustrated, that is posted to advertise or publicize something.

UserDownloads.name: UserDownloads
UserDownloads.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

DiscoverAction.name: DiscoverAction
DiscoverAction.help: The act of discovering/finding an object.

DepositAccount.name: DepositAccount
DepositAccount.help: A type of Bank Account with a main purpose of depositing funds to gain interest or other benefits.

EnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.name: EnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
EnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.help: Enumerates energy efficiency levels (also known as "classes" or "ratings") and certifications that are part of several international energy efficiency standards.

OrganizationRole.name: OrganizationRole
OrganizationRole.help: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

inputs.name: numberedPosition
inputs.label: Numbered Position
inputs.help: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

inputs.name: addressCountry
inputs.label: Address Country
inputs.help: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

inputs.name: addressLocality
inputs.label: Address Locality
inputs.help: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

inputs.name: addressRegion
inputs.label: Address Region
inputs.help: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

inputs.name: postOfficeBoxNumber
inputs.label: Post Office Box Number
inputs.help: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

inputs.name: postalCode
inputs.label: Postal Code
inputs.help: The postal code. For example, 94043.

inputs.name: streetAddress
inputs.label: Street Address
inputs.help: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

ReviewAction.name: ReviewAction
ReviewAction.help: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

inputs.name: resultReview
inputs.label: Result Review
inputs.help: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

TrainReservation.name: TrainReservation
TrainReservation.help: A reservation for train travel.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

HealthPlanNetwork.name: HealthPlanNetwork
HealthPlanNetwork.help: A US-style health insurance plan network.

inputs.name: healthPlanCostSharing
inputs.label: Health Plan Cost Sharing
inputs.help: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

inputs.name: healthPlanNetworkId
inputs.label: Health Plan Network Id
inputs.help: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

inputs.name: healthPlanNetworkTier
inputs.label: Health Plan Network Tier
inputs.help: The tier(s) for this network.

inputs.name: actionAccessibilityRequirement
inputs.label: Action Accessibility Requirement
inputs.help: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

inputs.name: expectsAcceptanceOf
inputs.label: Expects Acceptance Of
inputs.help: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

EnergyStarEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.name: EnergyStarEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
EnergyStarEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.help: Used to indicate whether a product is EnergyStar certified.

RentAction.name: RentAction
RentAction.help: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

inputs.name: landlord
inputs.label: Landlord
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

inputs.name: realEstateAgent
inputs.label: Real Estate Agent
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

MerchantReturnEnumeration.name: MerchantReturnEnumeration
MerchantReturnEnumeration.help: Enumerates several kinds of product return policies.

InteractAction.name: InteractAction
InteractAction.help: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

ShareAction.name: ShareAction
ShareAction.help: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

Canal.name: Canal
Canal.help: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

UserLikes.name: UserLikes
UserLikes.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

ClaimReview.name: ClaimReview
ClaimReview.help: A fact-checking review of claims made (or reported) in some creative work (referenced via itemReviewed).

inputs.name: claimReviewed
inputs.label: Claim Reviewed
inputs.help: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

ReportedDoseSchedule.name: ReportedDoseSchedule
ReportedDoseSchedule.help: A patient-reported or observed dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

PlanAction.name: PlanAction
PlanAction.help: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

inputs.name: scheduledTime
inputs.label: Scheduled Time
inputs.help: The time the object is scheduled to.

MoneyTransfer.name: MoneyTransfer
MoneyTransfer.help: The act of transferring money from one place to another place. This may occur electronically or physically.

inputs.name: amount
inputs.label: Amount
inputs.help: The amount of money.

inputs.name: beneficiaryBank
inputs.label: Beneficiary Bank
inputs.help: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

AudioObjectSnapshot.name: AudioObjectSnapshot
AudioObjectSnapshot.help: A specific and exact (byte-for-byte) version of an [[AudioObject]]. Two byte-for-byte identical files, for the purposes of this type, considered identical. If they have different embedded metadata the files will differ. Different external facts about the files, e.g. creator or dateCreated that aren't represented in their actual content, do not affect this notion of identity.

AnatomicalStructure.name: AnatomicalStructure
AnatomicalStructure.help: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

inputs.name: associatedPathophysiology
inputs.label: Associated Pathophysiology
inputs.help: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

inputs.name: bodyLocation
inputs.label: Body Location
inputs.help: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

inputs.name: connectedTo
inputs.label: Connected To
inputs.help: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

inputs.name: diagram
inputs.label: Diagram
inputs.help: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

inputs.name: partOfSystem
inputs.label: Part Of System
inputs.help: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

inputs.name: relatedCondition
inputs.label: Related Condition
inputs.help: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

inputs.name: relatedTherapy
inputs.label: Related Therapy
inputs.help: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

inputs.name: subStructure
inputs.label: Sub Structure
inputs.help: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

LearningResource.name: LearningResource
LearningResource.help:
The LearningResource type can be used to indicate [[CreativeWork]]s (whether physical or digital) that have a particular and explicit orientation towards learning, education, skill acquisition, and other educational purposes.

[[LearningResource]] is expected to be used as an addition to a primary type such as [[Book]], [[VideoObject]], [[Product]] etc.

[[EducationEvent]] serves a similar purpose for event-like things (e.g. a [[Trip]]). A [[LearningResource]] may be created as a result of an [[EducationEvent]], for example by recording one.

inputs.name: assesses
inputs.label: Assesses
inputs.help: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

inputs.name: competencyRequired
inputs.label: Competency Required
inputs.help: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

inputs.name: educationalAlignment
inputs.label: Educational Alignment
inputs.help:
An alignment to an established educational framework.

This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

inputs.name: educationalLevel
inputs.label: Educational Level
inputs.help: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

inputs.name: educationalUse
inputs.label: Educational Use
inputs.help: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

inputs.name: learningResourceType
inputs.label: Learning Resource Type
inputs.help: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

inputs.name: teaches
inputs.label: Teaches
inputs.help: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

MediaObject.name: MediaObject
MediaObject.help: A media object, such as an image, video, audio, or text object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

inputs.name: associatedArticle
inputs.label: Associated Article
inputs.help: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

inputs.name: bitrate
inputs.label: Bitrate
inputs.help: The bitrate of the media object.

inputs.name: contentSize
inputs.label: Content Size
inputs.help: File size in (mega/kilo)bytes.

inputs.name: contentUrl
inputs.label: Content Url
inputs.help: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: embedUrl
inputs.label: Embed Url
inputs.help: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

inputs.name: encodesCreativeWork
inputs.label: Encodes Creative Work
inputs.help: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

inputs.name: encodingFormat
inputs.label: Encoding Format
inputs.help:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

inputs.name: endTime
inputs.label: End Time
inputs.help: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

inputs.name: fileOf
inputs.label: File Of
inputs.help: Links from a File to its containing Object.

inputs.name: height
inputs.label: Height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.label: Ineligible Region
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: interpretedAsClaim
inputs.label: Interpreted As Claim
inputs.help: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

inputs.name: playerType
inputs.label: Player Type
inputs.help: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.label: Production Company
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: regionsAllowed
inputs.label: Regions Allowed
inputs.help: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

inputs.name: requiresSubscription
inputs.label: Requires Subscription
inputs.help: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

inputs.name: sha256
inputs.label: Sha 256
inputs.help: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'.

inputs.name: startTime
inputs.label: Start Time
inputs.help: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

inputs.name: uploadDate
inputs.label: Upload Date
inputs.help: Date (including time if available) when this media object was uploaded to this site.

inputs.name: width
inputs.label: Width
inputs.help: The width of the item.

Brand.name: Brand
Brand.help: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.label: Slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

UserInteraction.name: UserInteraction
UserInteraction.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

MovieClip.name: MovieClip
MovieClip.help: A short segment/part of a movie.

ComicSeries.name: ComicSeries
ComicSeries.help:
A sequential publication of comic stories under a
    	unifying title, for example "The Amazing Spider-Man" or "Groo the
    	Wanderer".

BusTrip.name: BusTrip
BusTrip.help: A trip on a commercial bus line.

inputs.name: arrivalBusStop
inputs.label: Arrival Bus Stop
inputs.help: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

inputs.name: busName
inputs.label: Bus Name
inputs.help: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

inputs.name: busNumber
inputs.label: Bus Number
inputs.help: The unique identifier for the bus.

inputs.name: departureBusStop
inputs.label: Departure Bus Stop
inputs.help: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

inputs.name: defaultValue
inputs.label: Default Value
inputs.help: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

inputs.name: maxValue
inputs.label: Max Value
inputs.help: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: minValue
inputs.label: Min Value
inputs.help: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: multipleValues
inputs.label: Multiple Values
inputs.help: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

inputs.name: readonlyValue
inputs.label: Readonly Value
inputs.help: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

inputs.name: stepValue
inputs.label: Step Value
inputs.help: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

inputs.name: valueMaxLength
inputs.label: Value Max Length
inputs.help: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

inputs.name: valueMinLength
inputs.label: Value Min Length
inputs.help: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

inputs.name: valueName
inputs.label: Value Name
inputs.help: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

inputs.name: valuePattern
inputs.label: Value Pattern
inputs.help: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

inputs.name: valueRequired
inputs.label: Value Required
inputs.help: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

ScreeningEvent.name: ScreeningEvent
ScreeningEvent.help: A screening of a movie or other video.

inputs.name: subtitleLanguage
inputs.label: Subtitle Language
inputs.help: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

inputs.name: videoFormat
inputs.label: Video Format
inputs.help: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

inputs.name: workPresented
inputs.label: Work Presented
inputs.help: The movie presented during this event.

NewsMediaOrganization.name: NewsMediaOrganization
NewsMediaOrganization.help: A News/Media organization such as a newspaper or TV station.

inputs.name: actionableFeedbackPolicy
inputs.label: Actionable Feedback Policy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

inputs.name: correctionsPolicy
inputs.label: Corrections Policy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

inputs.name: diversityPolicy
inputs.label: Diversity Policy
inputs.help: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

inputs.name: diversityStaffingReport
inputs.label: Diversity Staffing Report
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

inputs.name: ethicsPolicy
inputs.label: Ethics Policy
inputs.help: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

inputs.name: masthead
inputs.label: Masthead
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

inputs.name: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
inputs.label: Mission Coverage Priorities Policy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

inputs.name: noBylinesPolicy
inputs.label: No Bylines Policy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

inputs.name: ownershipFundingInfo
inputs.label: Ownership Funding Info
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

inputs.name: unnamedSourcesPolicy
inputs.label: Unnamed Sources Policy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

inputs.name: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
inputs.label: Verification Fact Checking Policy
inputs.help: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

DefinedTerm.name: DefinedTerm
DefinedTerm.help: A word, name, acronym, phrase, etc. with a formal definition. Often used in the context of category or subject classification, glossaries or dictionaries, product or creative work types, etc. Use the name property for the term being defined, use termCode if the term has an alpha-numeric code allocated, use description to provide the definition of the term.

inputs.name: inDefinedTermSet
inputs.label: In Defined Term Set
inputs.help: A [[DefinedTermSet]] that contains this term.

inputs.name: termCode
inputs.label: Term Code
inputs.help: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]].

AdvertiserContentArticle.name: AdvertiserContentArticle
AdvertiserContentArticle.help: An [[Article]] that an external entity has paid to place or to produce to its specifications. Includes [advertorials](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advertorial), sponsored content, native advertising and other paid content.

BusinessEntityType.name: BusinessEntityType
BusinessEntityType.help:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

Occupation.name: Occupation
Occupation.help: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

inputs.name: educationRequirements
inputs.label: Education Requirements
