inputs.help: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: estimatedSalary
inputs.label: Estimated Salary
inputs.help: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

inputs.name: experienceRequirements
inputs.label: Experience Requirements
inputs.help: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: occupationLocation
inputs.label: Occupation Location
inputs.help: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.label: Occupational Category
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: qualifications
inputs.label: Qualifications
inputs.help: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: responsibilities
inputs.label: Responsibilities
inputs.help: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: skills
inputs.label: Skills
inputs.help: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

OnDemandEvent.name: OnDemandEvent
OnDemandEvent.help: A publication event, e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

ReplaceAction.name: ReplaceAction
ReplaceAction.help: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

inputs.name: replacee
inputs.label: Replacee
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

inputs.name: replacer
inputs.label: Replacer
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

StructuredValue.name: StructuredValue
StructuredValue.help: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

WantAction.name: WantAction
WantAction.help: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

DanceGroup.name: DanceGroup
DanceGroup.help: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

MedicalSign.name: MedicalSign
MedicalSign.help: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

inputs.name: identifyingExam
inputs.label: Identifying Exam
inputs.help: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

inputs.name: identifyingTest
inputs.label: Identifying Test
inputs.help: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

PalliativeProcedure.name: PalliativeProcedure
PalliativeProcedure.help: A medical procedure intended primarily for palliative purposes, aimed at relieving the symptoms of an underlying health condition.

Episode.name: Episode
Episode.help: A media episode (e.g. TV, radio, video game) which can be part of a series or season.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.label: Actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.label: Actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: director
inputs.label: Director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.label: Directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: episodeNumber
inputs.label: Episode Number
inputs.help: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.label: Music By
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: partOfSeason
inputs.label: Part Of Season
inputs.help: The season to which this episode belongs.

inputs.name: partOfSeries
inputs.label: Part Of Series
inputs.help: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.label: Production Company
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.label: Trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

MedicalIntangible.name: MedicalIntangible
MedicalIntangible.help: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things in the medical space.

ArriveAction.name: ArriveAction
ArriveAction.help: The act of arriving at a place. An agent arrives at a destination from a fromLocation, optionally with participants.

inputs.name: acceptsReservations
inputs.label: Accepts Reservations
inputs.help: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

inputs.name: hasMenu
inputs.label: Has Menu
inputs.help: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

inputs.name: menu
inputs.label: Menu
inputs.help: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

inputs.name: servesCuisine
inputs.label: Serves Cuisine
inputs.help: The cuisine of the restaurant.

inputs.name: starRating
inputs.label: Star Rating
inputs.help: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

AnalysisNewsArticle.name: AnalysisNewsArticle
AnalysisNewsArticle.help: An AnalysisNewsArticle is a [[NewsArticle]] that, while based on factual reporting, incorporates the expertise of the author/producer, offering interpretations and conclusions.

TVSeason.name: TVSeason
TVSeason.help: Season dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

inputs.name: countryOfOrigin
inputs.label: Country Of Origin
inputs.help:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

inputs.name: partOfTVSeries
inputs.label: Part Of TV Series
inputs.help: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

inputs.name: titleEIDR
inputs.label: Title EIDR
inputs.help:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

ListItem.name: ListItem
ListItem.help: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

inputs.name: item
inputs.label: Item
inputs.help: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

inputs.name: nextItem
inputs.label: Next Item
inputs.help: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

inputs.name: position
inputs.label: Position
inputs.help: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

inputs.name: previousItem
inputs.label: Previous Item
inputs.help: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

Seat.name: Seat
Seat.help: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

inputs.name: seatNumber
inputs.label: Seat Number
inputs.help: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

inputs.name: seatRow
inputs.label: Seat Row
inputs.help: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

inputs.name: seatSection
inputs.label: Seat Section
inputs.help: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

inputs.name: seatingType
inputs.label: Seating Type
inputs.help: The type/class of the seat.

BroadcastFrequencySpecification.name: BroadcastFrequencySpecification
BroadcastFrequencySpecification.help: The frequency in MHz and the modulation used for a particular BroadcastService.

inputs.name: broadcastFrequencyValue
inputs.label: Broadcast Frequency Value
inputs.help: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

inputs.name: broadcastSignalModulation
inputs.label: Broadcast Signal Modulation
inputs.help: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

inputs.name: broadcastSubChannel
inputs.label: Broadcast Sub Channel
inputs.help: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

AcceptAction.name: AcceptAction
AcceptAction.help:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[RejectAction]]: The antonym of AcceptAction.

MobilePhoneStore.name: MobilePhoneStore
MobilePhoneStore.help: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.

HowToSection.name: HowToSection
HowToSection.help: A sub-grouping of steps in the instructions for how to achieve a result (e.g. steps for making a pie crust within a pie recipe).

inputs.name: steps
inputs.label: Steps
inputs.help: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

SellAction.name: SellAction
SellAction.help: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

inputs.name: buyer
inputs.label: Buyer
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

inputs.name: warrantyPromise
inputs.label: Warranty Promise
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

PodcastEpisode.name: PodcastEpisode
PodcastEpisode.help: A single episode of a podcast series.

Attorney.name: Attorney
Attorney.help: Professional service: Attorney. \n\nThis type is deprecated - [[LegalService]] is more inclusive and less ambiguous.

HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification.name: HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification
HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification.help: A description of costs to the patient under a given network or formulary.

inputs.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
inputs.label: Health Plan Coinsurance Option
inputs.help: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

inputs.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
inputs.label: Health Plan Coinsurance Rate
inputs.help: The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

inputs.name: healthPlanCopay
inputs.label: Health Plan Copay
inputs.help: The copay amount.

inputs.name: healthPlanCopayOption
inputs.label: Health Plan Copay Option
inputs.help: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

inputs.name: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
inputs.label: Health Plan Pharmacy Category
inputs.help: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

UKNonprofitType.name: UKNonprofitType
UKNonprofitType.help: UKNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the United Kingdom.

DrugPrescriptionStatus.name: DrugPrescriptionStatus
DrugPrescriptionStatus.help: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

Mass.name: Mass
Mass.help: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

MedicalTrial.name: MedicalTrial
MedicalTrial.help: A medical trial is a type of medical study that uses a scientific process to compare the safety and efficacy of medical therapies or medical procedures. In general, medical trials are controlled and subjects are allocated at random to the different treatment and/or control groups.

inputs.name: trialDesign
inputs.label: Trial Design
inputs.help: Specifics about the trial design (enumerated).

PreOrderAction.name: PreOrderAction
PreOrderAction.help: An agent orders a (not yet released) object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

SomeProducts.name: SomeProducts
SomeProducts.help: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

inputs.name: inventoryLevel
inputs.label: Inventory Level
inputs.help: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

Quantity.name: Quantity
Quantity.help: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 kg' or '4 milligrams'.

LifestyleModification.name: LifestyleModification
LifestyleModification.help: A process of care involving exercise, changes to diet, fitness routines, and other lifestyle changes aimed at improving a health condition.

BodyMeasurementTypeEnumeration.name: BodyMeasurementTypeEnumeration
BodyMeasurementTypeEnumeration.help: Enumerates types (or dimensions) of a person's body measurements, for example for fitting of clothes.

DataFeedItem.name: DataFeedItem
DataFeedItem.help: A single item within a larger data feed.

inputs.name: dateCreated
inputs.label: Date Created
inputs.help: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

inputs.name: dateDeleted
inputs.label: Date Deleted
inputs.help: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

inputs.name: dateModified
inputs.label: Date Modified
inputs.help: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

inputs.name: item
inputs.label: Item
inputs.help: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

House.name: House
House.help: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House).

inputs.name: numberOfRooms
inputs.label: Number Of Rooms
inputs.help:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

IndividualProduct.name: IndividualProduct
IndividualProduct.help: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

inputs.name: serialNumber
inputs.label: Serial Number
inputs.help: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

Continent.name: Continent
Continent.help: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

MusicRecording.name: MusicRecording
MusicRecording.help: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

inputs.name: byArtist
inputs.label: By Artist
inputs.help: The artist that performed this album or recording.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: inAlbum
inputs.label: In Album
inputs.help: The album to which this recording belongs.

inputs.name: inPlaylist
inputs.label: In Playlist
inputs.help: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

inputs.name: isrcCode
inputs.label: Isrc Code
inputs.help: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

inputs.name: recordingOf
inputs.label: Recording Of
inputs.help: The composition this track is a recording of.

PriceComponentTypeEnumeration.name: PriceComponentTypeEnumeration
PriceComponentTypeEnumeration.help: Enumerates different price components that together make up the total price for an offered product.

BackgroundNewsArticle.name: BackgroundNewsArticle
BackgroundNewsArticle.help: A [[NewsArticle]] providing historical context, definition and detail on a specific topic (aka "explainer" or "backgrounder"). For example, an in-depth article or frequently-asked-questions ([FAQ](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)) document on topics such as Climate Change or the European Union. Other kinds of background material from a non-news setting are often described using [[Book]] or [[Article]], in particular [[ScholarlyArticle]]. See also [[NewsArticle]] for related vocabulary from a learning/education perspective.

MedicalRiskFactor.name: MedicalRiskFactor
MedicalRiskFactor.help: A risk factor is anything that increases a person's likelihood of developing or contracting a disease, medical condition, or complication.

inputs.name: increasesRiskOf
inputs.label: Increases Risk Of
inputs.help: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

ExhibitionEvent.name: ExhibitionEvent
ExhibitionEvent.help: Event type: Exhibition event, e.g. at a museum, library, archive, tradeshow, ...

FoodService.name: FoodService
FoodService.help: A food service, like breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

Service.name: Service
Service.help: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.label: Area Served
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: audience
inputs.label: Audience
inputs.help: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

inputs.name: availableChannel
inputs.label: Available Channel
inputs.help: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

inputs.name: award
inputs.label: Award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.label: Brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.label: Broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: hasCertification
inputs.label: Has Certification
inputs.help: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

inputs.name: hasOfferCatalog
inputs.label: Has Offer Catalog
inputs.help: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

inputs.name: hoursAvailable
inputs.label: Hours Available
inputs.help: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

inputs.name: isRelatedTo
inputs.label: Is Related To
inputs.help: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isSimilarTo
inputs.label: Is Similar To
inputs.help: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: offers
inputs.label: Offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: produces
inputs.label: Produces
inputs.help: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.label: Provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: providerMobility
inputs.label: Provider Mobility
inputs.help: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: serviceArea
inputs.label: Service Area
inputs.help: The geographic area where the service is provided.

inputs.name: serviceAudience
inputs.label: Service Audience
inputs.help: The audience eligible for this service.

inputs.name: serviceOutput
inputs.label: Service Output
inputs.help: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

inputs.name: serviceType
inputs.label: Service Type
inputs.help: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.label: Slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: termsOfService
inputs.label: Terms Of Service
inputs.help: Human-readable terms of service documentation.

inputs.name: educationalRole
inputs.label: Educational Role
inputs.help: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

Nerve.name: Nerve
Nerve.help: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

inputs.name: branch
inputs.label: Branch
inputs.help: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

inputs.name: nerveMotor
inputs.label: Nerve Motor
inputs.help: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

inputs.name: sensoryUnit
inputs.label: Sensory Unit
inputs.help: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

inputs.name: sourcedFrom
inputs.label: Sourced From
inputs.help: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

inputs.name: albumProductionType
inputs.label: Album Production Type
inputs.help: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

inputs.name: albumRelease
inputs.label: Album Release
inputs.help: A release of this album.

inputs.name: albumReleaseType
inputs.label: Album Release Type
inputs.help: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

inputs.name: byArtist
inputs.label: By Artist
inputs.help: The artist that performed this album or recording.

MusicReleaseFormatType.name: MusicReleaseFormatType
MusicReleaseFormatType.help: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

RadioClip.name: RadioClip
RadioClip.help: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

EmployeeRole.name: EmployeeRole
EmployeeRole.help: A subclass of OrganizationRole used to describe employee relationships.

inputs.name: baseSalary
inputs.label: Base Salary
inputs.help: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

inputs.name: salaryCurrency
inputs.label: Salary Currency
inputs.help: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

CampingPitch.name: CampingPitch
CampingPitch.help:
A [[CampingPitch]] is an individual place for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically being part of a larger camping site, or [[Campground]].\n\n
In British English a campsite, or campground, is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual, family, group, or military unit can pitch a tent or park a camper; a campground may contain many campsites.
(Source: Wikipedia, see [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite).)\n\n
See also the dedicated [document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations](/docs/hotels.html).

Car.name: Car
Car.help: A car is a wheeled, self-powered motor vehicle used for transportation.

inputs.name: acrissCode
inputs.label: Acriss Code
inputs.help: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

inputs.name: roofLoad
inputs.label: Roof Load
inputs.help:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

EventAttendanceModeEnumeration.name: EventAttendanceModeEnumeration
EventAttendanceModeEnumeration.help: An EventAttendanceModeEnumeration value is one of potentially several modes of organising an event, relating to whether it is online or offline.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.label: Duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: median
inputs.label: Median
inputs.help: The median value.

inputs.name: percentile10
inputs.label: Percentile 10
inputs.help: The 10th percentile value.

inputs.name: percentile25
inputs.label: Percentile 25
inputs.help: The 25th percentile value.

inputs.name: percentile75
inputs.label: Percentile 75
inputs.help: The 75th percentile value.

inputs.name: percentile90
inputs.label: Percentile 90
inputs.help: The 90th percentile value.

ParentAudience.name: ParentAudience
ParentAudience.help: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

inputs.name: childMaxAge
inputs.label: Child Max Age
inputs.help: Maximal age of the child.

inputs.name: childMinAge
inputs.label: Child Min Age
inputs.help: Minimal age of the child.

Guide.name: Guide
Guide.help: [[Guide]] is a page or article that recommends specific products or services, or aspects of a thing for a user to consider. A [[Guide]] may represent a Buying Guide and detail aspects of products or services for a user to consider. A [[Guide]] may represent a Product Guide and recommend specific products or services. A [[Guide]] may represent a Ranked List and recommend specific products or services with ranking.

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.label: Review Aspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

MedicalEvidenceLevel.name: MedicalEvidenceLevel
MedicalEvidenceLevel.help: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

Report.name: Report
Report.help: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

inputs.name: reportNumber
inputs.label: Report Number
inputs.help: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

MonetaryAmount.name: MonetaryAmount
MonetaryAmount.help: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use [[PriceSpecification]] Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

inputs.name: currency
inputs.label: Currency
inputs.help: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: maxValue
inputs.label: Max Value
inputs.help: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: minValue
inputs.label: Min Value
inputs.help: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.label: Valid From
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.label: Valid Through
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: value
inputs.label: Value
inputs.help:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

ShippingDeliveryTime.name: ShippingDeliveryTime
ShippingDeliveryTime.help: ShippingDeliveryTime provides various pieces of information about delivery times for shipping.

inputs.name: businessDays
inputs.label: Business Days
inputs.help: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

inputs.name: cutoffTime
inputs.label: Cutoff Time
inputs.help: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

inputs.name: handlingTime
inputs.label: Handling Time
inputs.help: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

inputs.name: transitTime
inputs.label: Transit Time
inputs.help: The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride.name: MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride
MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride.help: A seasonal override of a return policy, for example used for holidays.

inputs.name: endDate
inputs.label: End Date
inputs.help: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: merchantReturnDays
inputs.label: Merchant Return Days
inputs.help: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

inputs.name: returnPolicyCategory
inputs.label: Return Policy Category
inputs.help: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

inputs.name: startDate
inputs.label: Start Date
inputs.help: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

Motel.name: Motel
Motel.help:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

PublicationIssue.name: PublicationIssue
PublicationIssue.help: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/09/schemaorg-support-for-bibliographic_2.html).

inputs.name: issueNumber
inputs.label: Issue Number
inputs.help: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

inputs.name: pageEnd
inputs.label: Page End
inputs.help: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

inputs.name: pageStart
inputs.label: Page Start
inputs.help: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

inputs.name: pagination
inputs.label: Pagination
inputs.help: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

MeasurementTypeEnumeration.name: MeasurementTypeEnumeration
MeasurementTypeEnumeration.help: Enumeration of common measurement types (or dimensions), for example "chest" for a person, "inseam" for pants, "gauge" for screws, or "wheel" for bicycles.

Artery.name: Artery
Artery.help: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

inputs.name: arterialBranch
inputs.label: Arterial Branch
inputs.help: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

inputs.name: supplyTo
inputs.label: Supply To
inputs.help: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

DayOfWeek.name: DayOfWeek
DayOfWeek.help:
The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer.

Originally, URLs from [GoodRelations](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1) were used (for [[Monday]], [[Tuesday]], [[Wednesday]], [[Thursday]], [[Friday]], [[Saturday]], [[Sunday]] plus a special entry for [[PublicHolidays]]); these have now been integrated directly into schema.org.

VoteAction.name: VoteAction
VoteAction.help: The act of expressing a preference from a fixed/finite/structured set of choices/options.

inputs.name: candidate
inputs.label: Candidate
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

DigitalDocumentPermissionType.name: DigitalDocumentPermissionType
DigitalDocumentPermissionType.help: A type of permission which can be granted for accessing a digital document.

HowToStep.name: HowToStep
HowToStep.help: A step in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It is an ordered list with HowToDirection and/or HowToTip items.

PaymentChargeSpecification.name: PaymentChargeSpecification
PaymentChargeSpecification.help: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

inputs.name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
inputs.label: Applies To Delivery Method
inputs.help: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

inputs.name: appliesToPaymentMethod
inputs.label: Applies To Payment Method
inputs.help: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

ItemListOrderType.name: ItemListOrderType
ItemListOrderType.help: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

FMRadioChannel.name: FMRadioChannel
FMRadioChannel.help: A radio channel that uses FM.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.label: Actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.label: Actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: characterAttribute
inputs.label: Character Attribute
inputs.help: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

inputs.name: cheatCode
inputs.label: Cheat Code
inputs.help: Cheat codes to the game.

inputs.name: containsSeason
inputs.label: Contains Season
inputs.help: A season that is part of the media series.

inputs.name: director
inputs.label: Director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.label: Directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: episode
inputs.label: Episode
inputs.help: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

inputs.name: episodes
inputs.label: Episodes
inputs.help: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

inputs.name: gameItem
inputs.label: Game Item
inputs.help: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

inputs.name: gameLocation
inputs.label: Game Location
inputs.help: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

inputs.name: gamePlatform
inputs.label: Game Platform
inputs.help: The electronic systems used to play video games.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.label: Music By
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: numberOfEpisodes
inputs.label: Number Of Episodes
inputs.help: The number of episodes in this season or series.

inputs.name: numberOfPlayers
inputs.label: Number Of Players
inputs.help: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

inputs.name: numberOfSeasons
inputs.label: Number Of Seasons
inputs.help: The number of seasons in this series.

inputs.name: playMode
inputs.label: Play Mode
inputs.help: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.label: Production Company
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: quest
inputs.label: Quest
inputs.help: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

inputs.name: season
inputs.label: Season
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: seasons
inputs.label: Seasons
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.label: Trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

inputs.name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
inputs.label: Fees And Commissions Specification
inputs.help: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

SendAction.name: SendAction
SendAction.help:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination. Related actions:

* [[ReceiveAction]]: The reciprocal of SendAction.
* [[GiveAction]]: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

inputs.name: deliveryMethod
inputs.label: Delivery Method
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.label: Recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

BioChemEntity.name: BioChemEntity
BioChemEntity.help: Any biological, chemical, or biochemical thing. For example: a protein; a gene; a chemical; a synthetic chemical.

inputs.name: associatedDisease
inputs.label: Associated Disease
inputs.help: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

inputs.name: bioChemInteraction
inputs.label: Bio Chem Interaction
inputs.help: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

inputs.name: bioChemSimilarity
inputs.label: Bio Chem Similarity
inputs.help: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

inputs.name: biologicalRole
inputs.label: Biological Role
inputs.help: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

inputs.name: funding
inputs.label: Funding
inputs.help: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

inputs.name: hasBioChemEntityPart
inputs.label: Has Bio Chem Entity Part
inputs.help: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

inputs.name: hasMolecularFunction
inputs.label: Has Molecular Function
inputs.help: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

inputs.name: hasRepresentation
inputs.label: Has Representation
inputs.help: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

inputs.name: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
inputs.label: Is Encoded By Bio Chem Entity
inputs.help: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

inputs.name: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
inputs.label: Is Involved In Biological Process
inputs.help: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

inputs.name: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
inputs.label: Is Located In Subcellular Location
inputs.help: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

inputs.name: isPartOfBioChemEntity
inputs.label: Is Part Of Bio Chem Entity
inputs.help: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

inputs.name: taxonomicRange
inputs.label: Taxonomic Range
inputs.help: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

SearchResultsPage.name: SearchResultsPage
SearchResultsPage.help: Web page type: Search results page.

MedicalIndication.name: MedicalIndication
MedicalIndication.help: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

inputs.name: tickerSymbol
inputs.label: Ticker Symbol
inputs.help: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

TreatmentIndication.name: TreatmentIndication
TreatmentIndication.help: An indication for treating an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

Invoice.name: Invoice
Invoice.help: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

inputs.name: accountId
inputs.label: Account Id
inputs.help: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

inputs.name: billingPeriod
inputs.label: Billing Period
inputs.help: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.label: Broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: confirmationNumber
inputs.label: Confirmation Number
inputs.help: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

inputs.name: customer
inputs.label: Customer
inputs.help: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

inputs.name: minimumPaymentDue
inputs.label: Minimum Payment Due
inputs.help: The minimum payment required at this time.

inputs.name: paymentDue
inputs.label: Payment Due
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentDueDate
inputs.label: Payment Due Date
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentMethod
inputs.label: Payment Method
inputs.help: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

inputs.name: paymentMethodId
inputs.label: Payment Method Id
inputs.help: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

inputs.name: paymentStatus
inputs.label: Payment Status
inputs.help: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.label: Provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: referencesOrder
inputs.label: References Order
inputs.help: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

inputs.name: scheduledPaymentDate
inputs.label: Scheduled Payment Date
inputs.help: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

inputs.name: totalPaymentDue
inputs.label: Total Payment Due
inputs.help: The total amount due.

LeaveAction.name: LeaveAction
LeaveAction.help:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: The antonym of LeaveAction.
* [[UnRegisterAction]]: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

inputs.name: event
inputs.label: Event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

MedicalRiskEstimator.name: MedicalRiskEstimator
MedicalRiskEstimator.help: Any rule set or interactive tool for estimating the risk of developing a complication or condition.

inputs.name: estimatesRiskOf
inputs.label: Estimates Risk Of
inputs.help: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

inputs.name: includedRiskFactor
inputs.label: Included Risk Factor
inputs.help: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

MoveAction.name: MoveAction
MoveAction.help:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

inputs.name: fromLocation
inputs.label: From Location
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

inputs.name: toLocation
inputs.label: To Location
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

inputs.name: mapType
inputs.label: Map Type
inputs.help: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

ContactPoint.name: ContactPoint
ContactPoint.help: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.label: Area Served
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: availableLanguage
inputs.label: Available Language
inputs.help: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

inputs.name: contactOption
inputs.label: Contact Option
inputs.help: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

inputs.name: contactType
inputs.label: Contact Type
inputs.help: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

inputs.name: email
inputs.label: Email
inputs.help: Email address.

inputs.name: faxNumber
inputs.label: Fax Number
inputs.help: The fax number.

inputs.name: hoursAvailable
inputs.label: Hours Available
inputs.help: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

inputs.name: productSupported
inputs.label: Product Supported
inputs.help: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

inputs.name: serviceArea
inputs.label: Service Area
inputs.help: The geographic area where the service is provided.

inputs.name: telephone
inputs.label: Telephone
inputs.help: The telephone number.

Audience.name: Audience
Audience.help: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

inputs.name: audienceType
inputs.label: Audience Type
inputs.help: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

inputs.name: geographicArea
inputs.label: Geographic Area
inputs.help: The geographic area associated with the audience.

FlightReservation.name: FlightReservation
FlightReservation.help: A reservation for air travel.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

inputs.name: boardingGroup
inputs.label: Boarding Group
inputs.help: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

inputs.name: passengerPriorityStatus
inputs.label: Passenger Priority Status
inputs.help: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

inputs.name: passengerSequenceNumber
inputs.label: Passenger Sequence Number
inputs.help: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

inputs.name: securityScreening
inputs.label: Security Screening
inputs.help: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

DigitalPlatformEnumeration.name: DigitalPlatformEnumeration
DigitalPlatformEnumeration.help: Enumerates some common technology platforms, for use with properties such as [[actionPlatform]]. It is not supposed to be comprehensive - when a suitable code is not enumerated here, textual or URL values can be used instead. These codes are at a fairly high level and do not deal with versioning and other nuance. Additional codes can be suggested [in github](https://github.com/schemaorg/schemaorg/issues/3057).

Reservation.name: Reservation
Reservation.help: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].

inputs.name: bookingAgent
inputs.label: Booking Agent
inputs.help: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

inputs.name: bookingTime
inputs.label: Booking Time
inputs.help: The date and time the reservation was booked.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.label: Broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: modifiedTime
inputs.label: Modified Time
inputs.help: The date and time the reservation was modified.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.label: Price Currency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: programMembershipUsed
inputs.label: Program Membership Used
inputs.help: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.label: Provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: reservationFor
inputs.label: Reservation For
inputs.help: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

inputs.name: reservationId
inputs.label: Reservation Id
inputs.help: A unique identifier for the reservation.

inputs.name: reservationStatus
inputs.label: Reservation Status
inputs.help: The current status of the reservation.

inputs.name: reservedTicket
inputs.label: Reserved Ticket
inputs.help: A ticket associated with the reservation.

inputs.name: totalPrice
inputs.label: Total Price
inputs.help:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: underName
inputs.label: Under Name
inputs.help: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

EntryPoint.name: EntryPoint
EntryPoint.help: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

inputs.name: actionApplication
inputs.label: Action Application
inputs.help: An application that can complete the request.

inputs.name: actionPlatform
inputs.label: Action Platform
inputs.help: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

inputs.name: application
inputs.label: Application
inputs.help: An application that can complete the request.

inputs.name: contentType
inputs.label: Content Type
inputs.help: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

inputs.name: encodingType
inputs.label: Encoding Type
inputs.help: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

inputs.name: httpMethod
inputs.label: Http Method
inputs.help: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

inputs.name: urlTemplate
inputs.label: Url Template
inputs.help: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

EmployerAggregateRating.name: EmployerAggregateRating
EmployerAggregateRating.help: An aggregate rating of an Organization related to its role as an employer.

Product.name: Product
Product.help: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

inputs.name: additionalProperty
inputs.label: Additional Property
inputs.help: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.label: Aggregate Rating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: asin
inputs.label: Asin
inputs.help:
An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).

Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

inputs.name: audience
inputs.label: Audience
inputs.help: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

inputs.name: award
inputs.label: Award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: awards
inputs.label: Awards
inputs.help: Awards won by or for this item.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.label: Brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: category
inputs.label: Category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: color
inputs.label: Color
inputs.help: The color of the product.

inputs.name: colorSwatch
inputs.label: Color Swatch
inputs.help: A color swatch image, visualizing the color of a [[Product]]. Should match the textual description specified in the [[color]] property. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

inputs.name: countryOfAssembly
inputs.label: Country Of Assembly
inputs.help: The place where the product was assembled.

inputs.name: countryOfLastProcessing
inputs.label: Country Of Last Processing
inputs.help: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

inputs.name: countryOfOrigin
inputs.label: Country Of Origin
inputs.help:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

inputs.name: depth
inputs.label: Depth
inputs.help: The depth of the item.

inputs.name: funding
inputs.label: Funding
inputs.help: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

inputs.name: gtin
inputs.label: Gtin
inputs.help:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties.

The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) expresses GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.).
Digital Links should be populated into the [[hasGS1DigitalLink]] attribute.

Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

inputs.name: gtin12
inputs.label: Gtin 12
inputs.help: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin13
inputs.label: Gtin 13
inputs.help: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin14
inputs.label: Gtin 14
inputs.help: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin8
inputs.label: Gtin 8
inputs.help: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: hasAdultConsideration
inputs.label: Has Adult Consideration
inputs.help: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

inputs.name: hasCertification
inputs.label: Has Certification
inputs.help: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

inputs.name: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
inputs.label: Has Energy Consumption Details
inputs.help: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

inputs.name: hasGS1DigitalLink
inputs.label: Has GS 1 Digital Link
inputs.help:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

inputs.name: hasMeasurement
inputs.label: Has Measurement
inputs.help: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

inputs.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
inputs.label: Has Merchant Return Policy
inputs.help: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

inputs.name: height
inputs.label: Height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: inProductGroupWithID
inputs.label: In Product Group With ID
inputs.help: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

inputs.name: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
inputs.label: Is Accessory Or Spare Part For
inputs.help: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

inputs.name: isConsumableFor
inputs.label: Is Consumable For
inputs.help: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

inputs.name: isFamilyFriendly
inputs.label: Is Family Friendly
inputs.help: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

inputs.name: isRelatedTo
inputs.label: Is Related To
inputs.help: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isSimilarTo
inputs.label: Is Similar To
inputs.help: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isVariantOf
inputs.label: Is Variant Of
inputs.help: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.label: Item Condition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: keywords
inputs.label: Keywords
inputs.help: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

inputs.name: logo
inputs.label: Logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: manufacturer
inputs.label: Manufacturer
inputs.help: The manufacturer of the product.

inputs.name: material
inputs.label: Material
inputs.help: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

inputs.name: mobileUrl
inputs.label: Mobile Url
inputs.help:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

inputs.name: model
inputs.label: Model
inputs.help: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

inputs.name: mpn
inputs.label: Mpn
inputs.help: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: negativeNotes
inputs.label: Negative Notes
inputs.help:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]].

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

inputs.name: nsn
inputs.label: Nsn
inputs.help: Indicates the [NATO stock number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NATO_Stock_Number) (nsn) of a [[Product]].

inputs.name: offers
inputs.label: Offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: pattern
inputs.label: Pattern
inputs.help: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

inputs.name: positiveNotes
inputs.label: Positive Notes
inputs.help:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

inputs.name: productID
inputs.label: Product ID
inputs.help: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

inputs.name: productionDate
inputs.label: Production Date
inputs.help: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

inputs.name: purchaseDate
inputs.label: Purchase Date
inputs.help: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

inputs.name: releaseDate
inputs.label: Release Date
inputs.help: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

inputs.name: review
inputs.label: Review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.label: Reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: size
inputs.label: Size
inputs.help: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

inputs.name: sku
inputs.label: Sku
inputs.help: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.label: Slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: weight
inputs.label: Weight
inputs.help: The weight of the product or person.

inputs.name: width
inputs.label: Width
inputs.help: The width of the item.

VitalSign.name: VitalSign
VitalSign.help: Vital signs are measures of various physiological functions in order to assess the most basic body functions.

TextObject.name: TextObject
TextObject.help: A text file. The text can be unformatted or contain markup, html, etc.

UpdateAction.name: UpdateAction
UpdateAction.help: The act of managing by changing/editing the state of the object.

inputs.name: collection
inputs.label: Collection
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

inputs.name: targetCollection
inputs.label: Target Collection
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

DeliveryEvent.name: DeliveryEvent
DeliveryEvent.help: An event involving the delivery of an item.

inputs.name: accessCode
inputs.label: Access Code
inputs.help: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

inputs.name: availableFrom
inputs.label: Available From
inputs.help: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

inputs.name: availableThrough
inputs.label: Available Through
inputs.help: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

inputs.name: hasDeliveryMethod
inputs.label: Has Delivery Method
inputs.help: Method used for delivery or shipping.

IndividualPhysician.name: IndividualPhysician
IndividualPhysician.help:
An individual medical practitioner. For their official address use [[address]], for affiliations to hospitals use [[hospitalAffiliation]]. 
The [[practicesAt]] property can be used to indicate [[MedicalOrganization]] hospitals, clinics, pharmacies etc. where this physician practices.

inputs.name: practicesAt
inputs.label: Practices At
inputs.help: A [[MedicalOrganization]] where the [[IndividualPhysician]] practices.

WPSideBar.name: WPSideBar
WPSideBar.help: A sidebar section of the page.

PhotographAction.name: PhotographAction
PhotographAction.help: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

UserTweets.name: UserTweets
UserTweets.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

TextDigitalDocument.name: TextDigitalDocument
TextDigitalDocument.help: A file composed primarily of text.

FindAction.name: FindAction
FindAction.help:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

* [[SearchAction]]: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

CableOrSatelliteService.name: CableOrSatelliteService
CableOrSatelliteService.help: A service which provides access to media programming like TV or radio. Access may be via cable or satellite.

Play.name: Play
Play.help: A play is a form of literature, usually consisting of dialogue between characters, intended for theatrical performance rather than just reading. Note: A performance of a Play would be a [[TheaterEvent]] or [[BroadcastEvent]] - the *Play* being the [[workPerformed]].

ReturnLabelSourceEnumeration.name: ReturnLabelSourceEnumeration
ReturnLabelSourceEnumeration.help: Enumerates several types of return labels for product returns.

ComicCoverArt.name: ComicCoverArt
ComicCoverArt.help: The artwork on the cover of a comic.

InvestmentFund.name: InvestmentFund
InvestmentFund.help: A company or fund that gathers capital from a number of investors to create a pool of money that is then re-invested into stocks, bonds and other assets.

inputs.name: iataCode
inputs.label: Iata Code
inputs.help: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

inputs.name: icaoCode
inputs.label: Icao Code
inputs.help: ICAO identifier for an airport.

InvestmentOrDeposit.name: InvestmentOrDeposit
InvestmentOrDeposit.help: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

inputs.name: amount
inputs.label: Amount
inputs.help: The amount of money.

DefinedTermSet.name: DefinedTermSet
DefinedTermSet.help: A set of defined terms, for example a set of categories or a classification scheme, a glossary, dictionary or enumeration.

inputs.name: hasDefinedTerm
inputs.label: Has Defined Term
inputs.help: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

BorrowAction.name: BorrowAction
BorrowAction.help:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.

Related actions:

* [[LendAction]]: Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

inputs.name: lender
inputs.label: Lender
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

MedicalClinic.name: MedicalClinic
MedicalClinic.help: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

inputs.name: availableService
inputs.label: Available Service
inputs.help: A medical service available from this provider.

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.label: Medical Specialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

Drug.name: Drug
Drug.help: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism. Here the term drug is used interchangeably with the term medicine although clinical knowledge makes a clear difference between them.

inputs.name: activeIngredient
inputs.label: Active Ingredient
inputs.help: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

inputs.name: administrationRoute
inputs.label: Administration Route
inputs.help: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

inputs.name: alcoholWarning
inputs.label: Alcohol Warning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

inputs.name: availableStrength
inputs.label: Available Strength
inputs.help: An available dosage strength for the drug.

inputs.name: breastfeedingWarning
inputs.label: Breastfeeding Warning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

inputs.name: clincalPharmacology
inputs.label: Clincal Pharmacology
inputs.help: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

inputs.name: clinicalPharmacology
inputs.label: Clinical Pharmacology
inputs.help: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

inputs.name: dosageForm
inputs.label: Dosage Form
inputs.help: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

inputs.name: doseSchedule
